1
00:00:06,966 --> 00:00:09,693
[Unplanned Trip is back after ten years]

2
00:00:09,693 --> 00:00:11,671
[Kicking off the whole thing...]
- Huh? - What?

3
00:00:11,671 --> 00:00:12,893
[A nationwide live kidnapping]

4
00:00:12,893 --> 00:00:14,536
So this was the plan.

5
00:00:14,536 --> 00:00:16,242
[A total jump scare]
- Huh? - What?

6
00:00:16,242 --> 00:00:17,293
[Hahahaha]

7
00:00:17,293 --> 00:00:18,878
So this was the plan.

8
00:00:18,878 --> 00:00:20,713
Hold on, count me out.

9
00:00:20,713 --> 00:00:22,316
[Yeah, you're going]
No way, not happening.

10
00:00:22,316 --> 00:00:23,483
What do I do now?

11
00:00:23,483 --> 00:00:25,318
- Is this real?
- What's happening?

12
00:00:25,318 --> 00:00:27,186
[Heavy snow alert hits on shoot day]
Oh my.

13
00:00:27,186 --> 00:00:28,927
[Powering through the weather]

14
00:00:28,927 --> 00:00:31,506
[Powering through lodging]
How much does a room cost?

15
00:00:31,506 --> 00:00:34,793
- Mind if we film just the meal?
- Go ahead.

16
00:00:34,793 --> 00:00:36,356
[Powering through the booking too]
All good?

17
00:00:36,356 --> 00:00:37,997
So tasty.

18
00:00:37,997 --> 00:00:39,226
[At last, some peace...]

19
00:00:39,226 --> 00:00:41,097
[Or so it seemed]

20
00:00:41,097 --> 00:00:42,677
I need to grab some underwear.

21
00:00:42,677 --> 00:00:44,458
Honestly, to be straight with you,

22
00:00:44,458 --> 00:00:46,998
- I got a perm yesterday.
- Right.

23
00:00:46,998 --> 00:00:49,041
So my stylist told me to skip washing

24
00:00:49,041 --> 00:00:52,517
- my hair through tomorrow.
- Skip washing?

25
00:00:52,517 --> 00:00:54,537
That's why I haven't showered.

26
00:00:54,537 --> 00:00:56,827
So my underwear right now...

27
00:00:56,827 --> 00:00:58,597
[Shocking confession...]
- This sucks. - So now...

28
00:00:58,597 --> 00:01:00,159
Was there a convenience store on the way?

29
00:01:00,159 --> 00:01:01,493
I think we head this way and turn here.

30
00:01:01,493 --> 00:01:02,855
- Yeah.
- Alright, let's roll.

31
00:01:02,855 --> 00:01:04,123
[For the sake of Woo Shik's underwear]

32
00:01:04,123 --> 00:01:05,124
[The journey kicks off]

33
00:01:05,124 --> 00:01:06,657
Hey, what's that?

34
00:01:06,657 --> 00:01:08,418
Man, it's freezing.

35
00:01:08,418 --> 00:01:10,326
Was there really a store nearby?

36
00:01:10,326 --> 00:01:12,765
We'll probably hit one along the way.

37
00:01:12,765 --> 00:01:14,493
Man, it's freezing.

38
00:01:14,493 --> 00:01:16,269
Can't spot it.

39
00:01:16,269 --> 00:01:18,570
Geez, freezing.

40
00:01:19,726 --> 00:01:21,438
Man, cold.

41
00:01:21,438 --> 00:01:22,438
So cold.

42
00:01:22,438 --> 00:01:23,776
- Colder than before, right?
- So cold.

43
00:01:23,776 --> 00:01:25,811
[Just as they're freezing
in the dropping temps...]

44
00:01:25,811 --> 00:01:28,092
Hey, 7-Eleven!

45
00:01:28,092 --> 00:01:30,316
[Finally, a store spotted]
There's a 7-Eleven!

46
00:01:30,316 --> 00:01:32,564
But if the underwear's 7,000 won,

47
00:01:32,564 --> 00:01:34,927
skipping that one bottle of soju
would've covered it...

48
00:01:34,927 --> 00:01:36,923
[Current balance: 4,750 won total]

49
00:01:36,923 --> 00:01:39,447
[Without that one bottle of soju,
the balance would be 8,250 won]

50
00:01:39,447 --> 00:01:41,661
- Okay, going in.
- Entering.

51
00:01:41,661 --> 00:01:43,375
[Will the underwear ring up under 4,750 won?]

52
00:01:43,375 --> 00:01:45,330
[Underwear hunt, attempt 1]
Let's head in.

53
00:01:46,259 --> 00:01:47,813
- Hello.
- Heart's pounding.

54
00:01:47,813 --> 00:01:49,613
- What's the price?
- Check this out.

55
00:01:49,613 --> 00:01:51,772
Isn't this what we're looking for?

56
00:01:51,772 --> 00:01:53,573
Huh? Dude, this isn't happening.

57
00:01:53,573 --> 00:01:56,366
9,900 won.

58
00:01:56,366 --> 00:01:58,444
9,900 won.

59
00:01:58,444 --> 00:01:59,971
[Even skipping one soju wouldn't cut it]

60
00:01:59,971 --> 00:02:01,047
Nothing else?

61
00:02:01,047 --> 00:02:02,426
Yeah.

62
00:02:02,426 --> 00:02:04,617
[Crushed]
This thing's nine-nine, basically 10,000 won.

63
00:02:04,617 --> 00:02:08,354
Skipping one bottle of soju
would've gotten me this.

64
00:02:08,354 --> 00:02:10,311
[He'd have to skip two bottles]
Let's bounce.

65
00:02:10,311 --> 00:02:11,451
Out we go.

66
00:02:11,451 --> 00:02:12,572
Take care.

67
00:02:12,572 --> 00:02:14,226
- Thanks.
- Have a good one.

68
00:02:14,226 --> 00:02:15,728
[Off to track down another store]

69
00:02:15,728 --> 00:02:17,612
- Did you score one?
- What was the damage?

70
00:02:17,612 --> 00:02:19,498
9,900 won.

71
00:02:19,498 --> 00:02:21,914
No chance.

72
00:02:22,835 --> 00:02:26,305
You should at least let me buy some underwear.

73
00:02:26,305 --> 00:02:28,119
[Now the complaints turn toward the crew]

74
00:02:28,119 --> 00:02:30,643
I'll end up sick at this rate.

75
00:02:30,643 --> 00:02:33,119
That's why you wash and reuse it.

76
00:02:33,119 --> 00:02:36,282
The thing is, it won't be dry by tomorrow.

77
00:02:36,282 --> 00:02:38,760
- You can dry it. There's a hairdryer too.
- Air's dry, it'll dry.

78
00:02:38,760 --> 00:02:41,220
Then I'd have to sleep next to this guy

79
00:02:41,220 --> 00:02:44,560
with nothing on?

80
00:02:44,560 --> 00:02:46,639
Why don't you ask to borrow underwear?

81
00:02:46,639 --> 00:02:48,719
Cover up with a mask.

82
00:02:48,719 --> 00:02:51,939
[Moving to the next spot]
Seriously, underwear's the bare minimum, right?

83
00:02:51,939 --> 00:02:54,140
Since I got the phone today,

84
00:02:54,140 --> 00:02:56,669
let me look up Daiso.

85
00:02:56,669 --> 00:02:58,337
It's all on the PC too, sis.

86
00:02:58,337 --> 00:02:59,538
True.

87
00:02:59,538 --> 00:03:01,793
- Right, we've got the PC.
- Watching this, our parents

88
00:03:01,793 --> 00:03:03,919
will be so upset.

89
00:03:03,919 --> 00:03:05,811
Same here.

90
00:03:05,811 --> 00:03:08,760
I can't roll
with one pair of underwear for a whole week.

91
00:03:08,760 --> 00:03:10,220
I'll buy them.

92
00:03:10,220 --> 00:03:11,660
3,500 won today?

93
00:03:11,660 --> 00:03:12,893
- Today too...
- We saved up, huh?

94
00:03:12,893 --> 00:03:16,522
Choi Woo Shik, washing underwear
as his final task of the day.

95
00:03:16,522 --> 00:03:18,924
[To avoid that fate...]

96
00:03:18,924 --> 00:03:20,260
[Underwear hunt, attempt 2]
Want to check that place?

97
00:03:20,260 --> 00:03:21,560
- A mart.
- Foreign market?

98
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:22,628
Yeah.

99
00:03:22,628 --> 00:03:24,997
Sir, do you carry underwear here?

100
00:03:24,997 --> 00:03:26,776
Got socks, but no underwear separately.

101
00:03:26,776 --> 00:03:27,833
No underwear at all?

102
00:03:27,833 --> 00:03:30,369
[This time, the bad news: no underwear at all]

103
00:03:30,369 --> 00:03:32,004
[And underwear hunt, attempt 3]
Huh? Looks like they might have it.

104
00:03:32,004 --> 00:03:33,207
Follow me.

105
00:03:33,207 --> 00:03:35,708
Everything's 9,900 won.

106
00:03:35,708 --> 00:03:37,969
[Once again, store's underwear is pricey]

107
00:03:37,969 --> 00:03:39,478
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

108
00:03:39,478 --> 00:03:40,959
[All underwear farming attempts: failed]

109
00:03:40,959 --> 00:03:44,256
The more I think about it,
this is just too much.

110
00:03:44,256 --> 00:03:45,885
There's our place.

111
00:03:45,885 --> 00:03:47,553
[Back at the lodging empty-handed]

112
00:03:47,553 --> 00:03:48,655
Gosh.

113
00:03:48,655 --> 00:03:51,524
From here on out, I really...

114
00:03:51,524 --> 00:03:53,359
I'll really do my best, I promise.

115
00:03:53,359 --> 00:03:57,726
Just hook me up with a few pairs of underwear
and some pajamas, please.

116
00:03:57,726 --> 00:04:01,067
And a razor too, just this once, please.

117
00:04:01,067 --> 00:04:04,070
I'll sell my soul and work my tail off.

118
00:04:04,070 --> 00:04:06,992
Help me out just this once.

119
00:04:06,992 --> 00:04:08,293
Just 20,000 won...

120
00:04:08,293 --> 00:04:11,266
30,000 won can cover everything at the market?

121
00:04:11,266 --> 00:04:12,793
Just give me 30,000 won, please.

122
00:04:12,793 --> 00:04:15,247
I'll work hard.

123
00:04:15,247 --> 00:04:17,550
[Sorry, Woo Shik]

124
00:04:17,550 --> 00:04:21,887
[8:03 PM, Seo Jun & Woo Shik's room]

125
00:04:21,887 --> 00:04:24,097
This feels gross.

126
00:04:24,097 --> 00:04:26,625
What am I supposed to do about these pants?

127
00:04:28,101 --> 00:04:29,227
They're soaked.

128
00:04:29,227 --> 00:04:31,271
[Even his one
and only pair of pants ended up soaked]

129
00:04:37,959 --> 00:04:39,478
Come out.

130
00:04:39,478 --> 00:04:41,073
You don't look weird. It's better than before.

131
00:04:41,073 --> 00:04:43,141
[With his only pants hung up to dry,
Woo Shik wraps himself in the hotel robe]

132
00:04:44,510 --> 00:04:45,545
[Demure...]

133
00:04:45,545 --> 00:04:47,213
I really want to snap a pic.

134
00:04:47,213 --> 00:04:49,348
[He's not bare underneath]

135
00:04:49,348 --> 00:04:50,488
What did you pull up the map on earlier?

136
00:04:50,488 --> 00:04:51,517
- Did you check this?
- Yeah.

137
00:04:51,517 --> 00:04:52,918
[Big sis tries to find Daiso for the youngest]

138
00:04:52,918 --> 00:04:56,187
Dongdaegu Daiso.

139
00:04:57,159 --> 00:04:59,368
- Dongdaegu Station Daiso.
- It's at the station?

140
00:04:59,368 --> 00:05:00,927
It's at Dongdaegu Station.

141
00:05:00,927 --> 00:05:02,808
Should we head out
and grab underwear right now?

142
00:05:02,808 --> 00:05:04,247
What time do they close?

143
00:05:04,247 --> 00:05:06,031
I feel bad, so I'll just run there alone.

144
00:05:06,031 --> 00:05:08,067
Oh, they're closed.

145
00:05:08,067 --> 00:05:11,407
[For today, no luck]

146
00:05:11,407 --> 00:05:12,847
Huh?

147
00:05:12,847 --> 00:05:13,626
What?

148
00:05:13,626 --> 00:05:15,141
- 3,000 won!
- 3,000 won!

149
00:05:15,141 --> 00:05:16,308
- 3,000 won!
- 3,000 won!

150
00:05:16,308 --> 00:05:17,660
- Nice.
- You good with boxers?

151
00:05:17,660 --> 00:05:19,645
- Yeah, perfect.
- Then tomorrow at nine...

152
00:05:19,645 --> 00:05:20,587
Yeah, tomorrow I'll...

153
00:05:20,587 --> 00:05:23,248
- So I don't have to wash it tonight.
- Right.

154
00:05:24,252 --> 00:05:26,719
If nobody picks up, we're done.

155
00:05:26,719 --> 00:05:27,827
Hold on a sec!

156
00:05:27,827 --> 00:05:28,927
How does this thing work?

157
00:05:28,927 --> 00:05:31,757
[Let me break this down for you...]
The phone pass got used.

158
00:05:31,757 --> 00:05:34,393
[Handed out earlier this morning]

159
00:05:34,393 --> 00:05:36,662
[Travel Restriction Notice]

160
00:05:36,662 --> 00:05:38,908
Yumi, mind reading number three?

161
00:05:38,908 --> 00:05:41,500
No phones allowed throughout the trip,

162
00:05:41,500 --> 00:05:44,948
except for one shot per day at the lodging.

163
00:05:44,948 --> 00:05:47,693
- So this means a pass is given, right?
- That's right.

164
00:05:47,693 --> 00:05:49,208
[Correct]
It's not just handed over.

165
00:05:49,208 --> 00:05:52,293
[There's a catch attached, not freely given]

166
00:05:52,293 --> 00:05:54,146
Here come the rules.

167
00:05:54,146 --> 00:05:55,927
- Okay.
- Okay, focus.

168
00:05:55,927 --> 00:05:57,917
The three of you share the phone pass

169
00:05:57,917 --> 00:06:00,735
for 90 seconds in relay style only.

170
00:06:00,735 --> 00:06:01,778
- Relay?
- Relay style?

171
00:06:01,778 --> 00:06:03,656
Only one person at a time can

172
00:06:03,656 --> 00:06:05,724
actually use the phone.

173
00:06:06,325 --> 00:06:11,831
[Take turns if you want]

174
00:06:11,831 --> 00:06:15,543
[Or one person hogs it all!]

175
00:06:15,543 --> 00:06:17,503
- 90 seconds total...
- 90 seconds total, that's it.

176
00:06:17,503 --> 00:06:19,444
- Let's skip the phone today then.
- We need a solid strategy...

177
00:06:19,444 --> 00:06:20,560
There's nobody I need to call,

178
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:21,984
so today's fine without it for me.

179
00:06:21,984 --> 00:06:24,003
Same here, no calls needed.

180
00:06:24,003 --> 00:06:26,178
But if it goes unanswered, we're toast.

181
00:06:26,178 --> 00:06:29,982
[The person Seo Jun's about to call is...]

182
00:06:29,982 --> 00:06:31,144
Want to head to Namwon?

183
00:06:31,144 --> 00:06:33,726
A buddy of mine has a place in Namwon.

184
00:06:33,726 --> 00:06:36,324
- Namwon?
- He kept begging me to visit Namwon.

185
00:06:36,324 --> 00:06:38,090
Let's do it.

186
00:06:38,090 --> 00:06:40,763
[Burning all 90 seconds on Seo Jun's buddy]
Searching can happen on the computer,

187
00:06:40,763 --> 00:06:43,593
so use the 90 seconds purely for the call.

188
00:06:43,593 --> 00:06:45,564
He'd better answer right away.

189
00:06:45,564 --> 00:06:48,380
No wait, here's how it goes,

190
00:06:48,380 --> 00:06:49,935
"Is tomorrow okay or not?"

191
00:06:49,935 --> 00:06:50,824
"Works."

192
00:06:50,824 --> 00:06:54,044
- Then 90 seconds run out before he finishes.
- Right.

193
00:06:54,044 --> 00:06:56,965
So you say "I'll call back tomorrow."

194
00:06:56,965 --> 00:06:59,285
But we can use the phone again tomorrow night.

195
00:06:59,285 --> 00:07:00,920
- Is this nighttime only?
- Yes.

196
00:07:00,920 --> 00:07:01,989
Oh really?

197
00:07:01,989 --> 00:07:04,950
Phones at night, benefits in the morning.

198
00:07:04,950 --> 00:07:06,619
- Heading to Daiso tomorrow, right?
- Yeah.

199
00:07:06,619 --> 00:07:09,755
While shopping,
just borrow a phone at the info desk.

200
00:07:09,755 --> 00:07:11,004
[So smart]
Yeah, that works too.

201
00:07:11,004 --> 00:07:12,545
Just try calling him first.

202
00:07:12,545 --> 00:07:14,573
Hold up, what should I even say?

203
00:07:14,573 --> 00:07:16,328
- So I'm filming a show right now.
- Yeah.

204
00:07:16,328 --> 00:07:17,560
Can we crash at your Namwon place?

205
00:07:17,560 --> 00:07:19,365
[Friend stand-in]
Huh? What's that mean?

206
00:07:19,365 --> 00:07:22,573
- A simulation.
- I'm in Daegu and want to head to Namwon,

207
00:07:22,573 --> 00:07:24,193
so can we borrow your place?

208
00:07:24,193 --> 00:07:25,371
What're you doing there?

209
00:07:25,371 --> 00:07:27,072
Address...

210
00:07:27,072 --> 00:07:29,002
I'll explain when I get there.

211
00:07:30,092 --> 00:07:32,292
The address is a must too.

212
00:07:32,292 --> 00:07:33,912
- Address and...
- Hang on.

213
00:07:33,912 --> 00:07:36,715
[Friend's number, Availability, Namwon address]
Dongdaegu to Namwon Terminal.

214
00:07:36,715 --> 00:07:38,751
Whether we can stay...

215
00:07:38,751 --> 00:07:41,487
Going from Daegu to Namwon...

216
00:07:41,487 --> 00:07:43,359
Do you really have to do it that way?

217
00:07:43,359 --> 00:07:45,965
- One sec.
- Public transit might not even reach there.

218
00:07:45,965 --> 00:07:49,428
Seobu Terminal runs intercity buses!

219
00:07:49,428 --> 00:07:52,495
[Yumi dives straight into searching]
The route from Daegu Seobu goes...

220
00:07:52,495 --> 00:07:54,460
through Geochang, Hamyang, Namwon, Yeosu.

221
00:07:54,460 --> 00:07:56,814
A direct line does exist, though.

222
00:07:56,814 --> 00:07:58,675
Even without the place, Namwon's still on!

223
00:07:58,675 --> 00:07:59,735
Should we just head out then?

224
00:07:59,735 --> 00:08:02,541
- Make the call once we're rolling.
- Okay.

225
00:08:02,541 --> 00:08:05,270
[Will the friend even pick up...]

226
00:08:05,270 --> 00:08:06,390
Here we go.

227
00:08:06,390 --> 00:08:07,995
- Here we go.
- Ready, start.

228
00:08:07,995 --> 00:08:09,949
[Timer running]
- Started? - Yes.

229
00:08:09,949 --> 00:08:13,162
[Into the contacts first]

230
00:08:13,162 --> 00:08:15,193
Hurry up...

231
00:08:15,193 --> 00:08:16,560
Why's the search taking forever?

232
00:08:16,560 --> 00:08:17,662
Where's the number?

233
00:08:17,662 --> 00:08:19,425
[Call going out]
Should I jot it down?

234
00:08:19,425 --> 00:08:21,126
Why can't I find the number?

235
00:08:21,126 --> 00:08:23,796
Get the number written down first.

236
00:08:23,796 --> 00:08:26,620
[Finally jotting the number down]

237
00:08:28,460 --> 00:08:30,326
- Yeah.
- He picked up.

238
00:08:30,326 --> 00:08:32,026
- He picked up.
- Hey.

239
00:08:32,026 --> 00:08:33,903
- Yeah.
- Quick question coming.

240
00:08:33,903 --> 00:08:36,062
Is the Namwon place open for us?

241
00:08:36,062 --> 00:08:38,092
We're filming Unplanned Trip right now.

242
00:08:38,092 --> 00:08:40,283
The plan is moving from Daegu down to Namwon.

243
00:08:40,283 --> 00:08:42,147
Is that Namwon place up for grabs?

244
00:08:42,147 --> 00:08:43,132
Yeah, it's all yours.

245
00:08:43,132 --> 00:08:45,292
[At least it's a yes!]
Send the address.

246
00:08:45,292 --> 00:08:47,293
Wait, you're heading there right now?

247
00:08:47,293 --> 00:08:48,587
No, tomorrow's the day.

248
00:08:48,587 --> 00:08:49,992
Tomorrow? Got it.

249
00:08:49,992 --> 00:08:51,991
- Address!
- Is the place empty over there?

250
00:08:51,991 --> 00:08:53,226
- Empty as can be.
- Address!

251
00:08:53,226 --> 00:08:54,452
Send the address.

252
00:08:54,452 --> 00:08:56,259
- Huh, for real?
- Yeah.

253
00:08:56,259 --> 00:08:57,493
Alright, hang tight.

254
00:08:57,493 --> 00:08:58,493
- No.
- No.

255
00:08:58,493 --> 00:08:59,753
- No time, address.
- I haven't been drinking.

256
00:08:59,753 --> 00:09:00,972
- Address!
- Yeah, okay.

257
00:09:00,972 --> 00:09:01,913
- Don't hang up.
- The thing is, we're...

258
00:09:01,913 --> 00:09:03,232
Hold on.

259
00:09:03,232 --> 00:09:05,137
40 seconds left on the clock.

260
00:09:05,137 --> 00:09:08,540
Fine, I'll text it over.

261
00:09:08,540 --> 00:09:10,660
No, the address has to come right now.

262
00:09:10,660 --> 00:09:12,526
- All right, okay.
- Yeah.

263
00:09:12,526 --> 00:09:14,995
Ten seconds on the clock.

264
00:09:14,995 --> 00:09:16,693
Oh yeah?

265
00:09:16,693 --> 00:09:18,916
- Tomorrow daytime works.
- Eight.

266
00:09:18,916 --> 00:09:20,675
- The next call comes from us.
- Seven.

267
00:09:20,675 --> 00:09:23,326
- I'm drinking right now.
- Six, five, four.

268
00:09:23,326 --> 00:09:24,626
- Chang Su's here too.
- It's all good.

269
00:09:24,626 --> 00:09:25,916
So it's a go?

270
00:09:25,916 --> 00:09:28,393
[Phone time over]
- Yeah, all set. - Empty over there?

271
00:09:28,393 --> 00:09:31,555
[Phones confiscated, no exceptions]
- Okay. - Thanks so much.

272
00:09:31,555 --> 00:09:32,956
- He's usually...
- Got the number?

273
00:09:32,956 --> 00:09:34,500
- Yeah, it's written.
- Yeah.

274
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:36,326
- It's down.
- What was that?

275
00:09:36,326 --> 00:09:39,359
- What was that?
- He kept trying to hang up...

276
00:09:39,359 --> 00:09:41,340
- Tomorrow morning then.
- It checks out.

277
00:09:41,340 --> 00:09:43,742
A morning call seals the address.

278
00:09:43,742 --> 00:09:45,260
- Yeah, it works out.
- Yeah, okay.

279
00:09:45,260 --> 00:09:46,612
What a relief.

280
00:09:46,612 --> 00:09:50,049
[Route unknown but...
Namwon lodging is locked in!]

281
00:09:50,049 --> 00:09:51,550
[Ugh...]

282
00:09:51,550 --> 00:09:53,160
The stress on this is real.

283
00:09:53,160 --> 00:09:55,788
90 seconds fly by, way too fast.

284
00:09:55,788 --> 00:09:57,756
[Figuring out how
to reach Namwon comes next...]

285
00:09:57,756 --> 00:09:59,659
- Because...
- Seobu Terminal.

286
00:09:59,659 --> 00:10:01,192
Right here.

287
00:10:02,019 --> 00:10:04,619
- Namwon Public Bus Terminal.
- Yeah.

288
00:10:04,619 --> 00:10:07,085
Not a ton of timeslots here.

289
00:10:07,085 --> 00:10:09,068
- The 11 o'clock one's the pick.
- Actually...

290
00:10:09,068 --> 00:10:11,560
- Hold on, that's the deluxe bus.
- 13,000 won apart though?

291
00:10:11,560 --> 00:10:13,673
A 3,300 won gap, isn't it?

292
00:10:13,673 --> 00:10:16,442
Tomorrow's lodging cost is zero.

293
00:10:16,442 --> 00:10:17,726
- Deluxe bus it is.
- That tracks.

294
00:10:17,726 --> 00:10:20,045
- Deluxe bus.
- Deluxe bus.

295
00:10:21,462 --> 00:10:23,660
The 3,300 won gap though,

296
00:10:23,660 --> 00:10:26,251
multiplied by three of us hits 9,900 won.

297
00:10:26,251 --> 00:10:28,220
A single pair of 7-Eleven underwear.

298
00:10:28,220 --> 00:10:30,783
Daiso, just Daiso...

299
00:10:30,783 --> 00:10:32,383
Wait, that's right?

300
00:10:32,383 --> 00:10:34,723
- It's right.
- Three pairs at Daiso for the same price.

301
00:10:34,723 --> 00:10:36,903
Deluxe bus or one pair of underwear?

302
00:10:36,903 --> 00:10:39,264
The underwear wins.

303
00:10:39,264 --> 00:10:40,643
- Got it.
- Regular bus then.

304
00:10:40,643 --> 00:10:42,382
The 12:30 one's the pick.

305
00:10:42,382 --> 00:10:43,936
Right, the 12:30 ride.

306
00:10:43,936 --> 00:10:46,659
- 2:30 leaves enough time.
- Right, working off the schedule...

307
00:10:46,659 --> 00:10:50,075
Hold on, where's Seobu Terminal at?

308
00:10:50,842 --> 00:10:52,760
25 minutes.

309
00:10:52,760 --> 00:10:54,642
- Subway works.
- Subway, the subway.

310
00:10:54,642 --> 00:10:56,163
The subway's the move.

311
00:10:56,163 --> 00:10:58,618
No phone means no screenshot option.
Write there.

312
00:10:58,618 --> 00:10:59,992
Scratch that. Write it down.

313
00:10:59,992 --> 00:11:01,523
Just in case, you know?

314
00:11:01,523 --> 00:11:04,343
We need to have time
to buy underwear for Woo Shik.

315
00:11:04,343 --> 00:11:06,822
Seobu Terminal Station, that's the stop.

316
00:11:06,822 --> 00:11:09,927
Exit 3, doors open right.

317
00:11:09,927 --> 00:11:11,860
Why even write that down?

318
00:11:11,860 --> 00:11:13,132
112 meters on foot.

319
00:11:13,132 --> 00:11:15,400
Right, Seobu Terminal Exit 3.

320
00:11:15,400 --> 00:11:16,880
[Directions noted down]
Exit 3, then out.

321
00:11:16,880 --> 00:11:18,704
[Namwon house]
But what if the address is

322
00:11:18,704 --> 00:11:20,401
way out in the sticks...

323
00:11:20,401 --> 00:11:22,361
- Namwon?
- How do we even get in?

324
00:11:22,361 --> 00:11:23,781
Hitchhiking solves it.

325
00:11:23,781 --> 00:11:25,261
That checks out.

326
00:11:25,261 --> 00:11:27,193
- Hitchhiking?
- Yeah.

327
00:11:27,193 --> 00:11:29,681
Tomorrow's lodging cost is saved either way.

328
00:11:29,681 --> 00:11:31,121
- That's true.
- What now?

329
00:11:31,121 --> 00:11:32,827
- Back in Seoul later...
- Not just lodging.

330
00:11:32,827 --> 00:11:35,340
Dinner runs cheap too, with that math.

331
00:11:35,340 --> 00:11:37,789
Pork belly party tomorrow, that's the plan.

332
00:11:37,789 --> 00:11:39,927
[Heart racing...]

333
00:11:39,927 --> 00:11:41,693
We should head out at 10:30.

334
00:11:41,693 --> 00:11:42,793
10:30.

335
00:11:42,793 --> 00:11:44,930
- Is 10:30 cutting it close?
- Right?

336
00:11:44,930 --> 00:11:46,509
- Let's leave at 10:00.
- 10:00 it is.

337
00:11:46,509 --> 00:11:48,390
Heading out at 10:00. Right, tomorrow.

338
00:11:48,390 --> 00:11:50,549
- Right before we head out.
- Before takeoff.

339
00:11:50,549 --> 00:11:52,526
So tomorrow when we hand out allowance,

340
00:11:52,526 --> 00:11:54,370
we'll do the benefit draw too.

341
00:11:54,370 --> 00:11:55,930
Ten minutes, only ten minutes?

342
00:11:55,930 --> 00:11:57,310
- Quick.
- It'll be quick.

343
00:11:57,310 --> 00:11:58,090
- Oh really?
- Yeah.

344
00:11:58,090 --> 00:12:01,747
- No "you lose" cards, right?
- No.

345
00:12:01,747 --> 00:12:04,092
Wonder what the benefits are.

346
00:12:04,092 --> 00:12:06,018
[9:35 PM, Seo Jun & Woo Shik's room]

347
00:12:06,018 --> 00:12:07,741
You showering now or what's the plan?

348
00:12:07,741 --> 00:12:09,222
Huh? I'll watch first, then shower.

349
00:12:09,222 --> 00:12:10,426
- Cool.
- Yeah.

350
00:12:10,426 --> 00:12:11,959
- You guys all showered?
- Yeah.

351
00:12:11,959 --> 00:12:13,493
That was fast.

352
00:12:13,493 --> 00:12:17,301
[Rewatching the live that pranked them today]
I think now's the right time to head out.

353
00:12:17,301 --> 00:12:19,321
Alright, here we go.

354
00:12:19,321 --> 00:12:20,465
Writer Kim Dae Ju.

355
00:12:20,465 --> 00:12:23,026
Congrats on 20 years as a writer!

356
00:12:23,026 --> 00:12:24,115
Thank you so much.

357
00:12:24,115 --> 00:12:25,904
- Send your shoutouts, everyone!
- Solid acting.

358
00:12:25,904 --> 00:12:27,372
[Stunned]
Wait, is that really a thing?

359
00:12:27,372 --> 00:12:28,807
Sneaky devils, all of them.

360
00:12:28,807 --> 00:12:30,860
- Congrats!
- Thank you.

361
00:12:30,860 --> 00:12:32,778
Seriously, total scammers.

362
00:12:32,778 --> 00:12:36,665
- This whole thing is fake?
- Look at the setup.

363
00:12:36,665 --> 00:12:38,293
Knowing them,

364
00:12:38,293 --> 00:12:39,751
they'd go "Oh really?"

365
00:12:39,751 --> 00:12:42,760
[Figured it out]

366
00:12:42,760 --> 00:12:46,097
[Slowly plotting with the viewers]
Four questions, but the answers are locked in.

367
00:12:46,097 --> 00:12:49,238
So that was scripted too.

368
00:12:49,238 --> 00:12:52,426
- Oh right, the travel thing...
- No wonder travel kept popping up.

369
00:12:52,426 --> 00:12:54,766
- Travel's coming up a lot.
- Don't post so fast like now.

370
00:12:54,766 --> 00:12:56,201
Nail the timing.

371
00:12:56,201 --> 00:12:59,638
[Even they think it's hilarious]

372
00:12:59,638 --> 00:13:01,206
[Back to the congrats charade]
Thank you.

373
00:13:01,206 --> 00:13:04,209
Everyone commented, "Congrats, Mr. Kim!"

374
00:13:05,444 --> 00:13:07,112
I have to pretend I didn't know

375
00:13:07,112 --> 00:13:09,181
they were coming down to congratulate me.

376
00:13:09,181 --> 00:13:12,195
[Speechless]
We should act surprised too.

377
00:13:12,195 --> 00:13:15,320
To celebrate Mr. Kim's 20th anniversary,

378
00:13:15,320 --> 00:13:19,078
- the celebration crew has arrived!
- Look at the staff acting!

379
00:13:20,359 --> 00:13:22,526
Hello.

380
00:13:22,526 --> 00:13:24,959
We look like total fools.

381
00:13:24,959 --> 00:13:26,998
Like complete idiots.

382
00:13:28,300 --> 00:13:30,867
[Spaced out...]

383
00:13:31,626 --> 00:13:34,473
They were really pulling it off.

384
00:13:34,473 --> 00:13:36,008
[The betrayal hits harder on rewatch]

385
00:13:36,008 --> 00:13:38,094
They're monsters.

386
00:13:38,094 --> 00:13:39,123
See you tomorrow.

387
00:13:39,123 --> 00:13:40,746
Yeah.

388
00:13:40,746 --> 00:13:43,849
[After the rewatch wraps...]

389
00:13:43,849 --> 00:13:46,470
[Yumi parks herself at the computer]

390
00:13:47,193 --> 00:13:49,288
[Gwanghallu, Wolmae's house, pond coin wish]
Oh, a coin?

391
00:13:49,288 --> 00:13:53,092
[Looking up Namwon's Gwanghallu Garden]

392
00:13:53,092 --> 00:13:55,682
[Right after the phone perk]
Namwon... places to check out...

393
00:13:55,682 --> 00:13:57,042
Gwanghallu!

394
00:13:57,042 --> 00:13:58,062
What is that?

395
00:13:58,062 --> 00:13:59,662
Isn't that the one?

396
00:13:59,662 --> 00:14:01,332
Chunhyang...

397
00:14:02,034 --> 00:14:03,634
- That's gorgeous.
- This spot's pretty.

398
00:14:03,634 --> 00:14:04,683
[The exact place they mentioned earlier]

399
00:14:04,683 --> 00:14:06,171
That's where we should go.

400
00:14:06,171 --> 00:14:08,640
[Free entry if you wear a hanbok, but...]

401
00:14:08,640 --> 00:14:10,342
50,000 won?

402
00:14:10,342 --> 00:14:12,560
[Rubbing her nose]

403
00:14:12,560 --> 00:14:14,612
But this still costs money.

404
00:14:16,154 --> 00:14:17,827
Here's why Yeonggwang Gulbi got famous.

405
00:14:17,827 --> 00:14:20,552
[Looking up Yeonggwang Gulbi for Woo Shik]
Chilsan croaker hits Beopseongpo...

406
00:14:20,552 --> 00:14:22,228
[Tapping]

407
00:14:22,228 --> 00:14:24,259
Not bad at all.

408
00:14:24,259 --> 00:14:26,460
[What are they up to?]

409
00:14:26,460 --> 00:14:28,593
[The younger guys are deep in their game]

410
00:14:28,593 --> 00:14:31,396
[Game over]
Man, one shot and it's done.

411
00:14:31,396 --> 00:14:33,833
[That was a brutal battle...]

412
00:14:33,833 --> 00:14:35,292
Let's hit the hay.

413
00:14:35,292 --> 00:14:37,112
You're done already?

414
00:14:37,112 --> 00:14:38,112
Call it.

415
00:14:38,112 --> 00:14:39,426
Yeah?

416
00:14:39,426 --> 00:14:42,812
Tomorrow matters more than this.

417
00:14:42,812 --> 00:14:45,843
Hey, no phones, so what about an alarm?

418
00:14:45,843 --> 00:14:46,886
[Deep in thought...]

419
00:14:46,886 --> 00:14:49,765
Try Google for an alarm...

420
00:14:50,482 --> 00:14:51,817
An alarm service.

421
00:14:51,817 --> 00:14:53,719
[Tapping]

422
00:14:53,719 --> 00:14:56,255
[Under Woo Shik's direction]

423
00:14:56,255 --> 00:14:57,452
[Site found]
Got it.

424
00:14:57,452 --> 00:14:59,226
- This one?
- Yeah.

425
00:14:59,226 --> 00:15:00,793
Up at 7:30 for us.

426
00:15:00,793 --> 00:15:03,292
[Why on earth?]
7:30?

427
00:15:03,292 --> 00:15:04,932
I'll go grab that stuff.

428
00:15:04,932 --> 00:15:06,372
Grab what?

429
00:15:06,372 --> 00:15:07,699
You know, cereal and stuff.

430
00:15:07,699 --> 00:15:09,026
Oh, really?

431
00:15:09,026 --> 00:15:12,259
[Free snack bar available downstairs]

432
00:15:12,259 --> 00:15:13,605
Fingers crossed it'll ring.

433
00:15:13,605 --> 00:15:16,026
[Pinning their hopes on the alarm site]

434
00:15:16,026 --> 00:15:18,009
Think that'll wake us up?

435
00:15:18,009 --> 00:15:21,193
[No speaker, headset cranked up close]

436
00:15:21,193 --> 00:15:23,849
[Lights out in the younger guys' room too]

437
00:15:23,849 --> 00:15:28,927
[Night one is settling in deep...]

438
00:15:28,927 --> 00:15:30,756
[3:40 AM, Yumi's room]

439
00:15:30,756 --> 00:15:33,492
[Tossing]

440
00:15:33,492 --> 00:15:35,727
[Checking the time]

441
00:15:35,727 --> 00:15:37,162
[4:40 AM, Seo Jun and Woo Shik's room]

442
00:15:37,162 --> 00:15:39,205
[Seo Jun]

443
00:15:40,465 --> 00:15:46,605
[As they toss all night,
morning keeps creeping in]

444
00:15:47,239 --> 00:15:50,509
[Seo Jun's up first]

445
00:15:50,509 --> 00:15:54,846
[Heads straight down for breakfast]

446
00:15:55,547 --> 00:15:58,393
[Hands full]

447
00:15:58,393 --> 00:16:00,652
Hey Woo Shik, dig in.

448
00:16:00,652 --> 00:16:03,187
[Woo Shik's waking up]

449
00:16:04,122 --> 00:16:07,359
[Looks like he slept like a rock]

450
00:16:07,359 --> 00:16:09,963
[Shaking off the sleep]

451
00:16:12,164 --> 00:16:15,976
[Bit of a rough setup]

452
00:16:15,976 --> 00:16:18,369
[Tension up]
Cereal.

453
00:16:19,904 --> 00:16:22,040
Thanks, man.

454
00:16:22,040 --> 00:16:24,526
[Seo Jun's already inhaling it like gukbap]

455
00:16:24,526 --> 00:16:26,359
Is the milk that kind?

456
00:16:26,359 --> 00:16:29,080
- Huh?
- The milk's that one...

457
00:16:29,080 --> 00:16:32,884
[Takes a bite first]

458
00:16:32,884 --> 00:16:35,154
Easy-on-the-stomach milk?

459
00:16:35,154 --> 00:16:36,744
What?

460
00:16:37,422 --> 00:16:39,184
[Sticking with it]
Easy-digest milk.

461
00:16:39,184 --> 00:16:41,026
No clue, just eat.

462
00:16:41,026 --> 00:16:43,662
Without that milk in the morning,

463
00:16:43,662 --> 00:16:45,293
I'll have the runs all day.

464
00:16:45,293 --> 00:16:46,339
Then skip it.

465
00:16:46,339 --> 00:16:47,365
[No]

466
00:16:47,365 --> 00:16:50,135
[Should eat while you can]

467
00:16:50,135 --> 00:16:52,437
[Rub]

468
00:16:52,437 --> 00:16:54,606
[Woo Shik's hands work magic]

469
00:16:54,606 --> 00:16:57,196
[The set time rolls around fast]

470
00:16:57,927 --> 00:17:01,079
[9:50 AM, Meeting time]

471
00:17:02,447 --> 00:17:06,860
[Right on time, knock at Yumi's room first]

472
00:17:06,860 --> 00:17:09,154
- We're starting now. Head over there...
- Oh, yes.

473
00:17:09,154 --> 00:17:10,527
[Heads right to the younger guys' room]

474
00:17:10,527 --> 00:17:12,567
- Hey Yumi, sleep okay?
- Slept like a baby.

475
00:17:12,567 --> 00:17:14,686
- Glad to hear it.
- Thought I wouldn't wake up.

476
00:17:14,686 --> 00:17:16,595
With no alarm and all,

477
00:17:16,595 --> 00:17:17,687
- I woke up every two hours.
- Who's there?

478
00:17:17,687 --> 00:17:18,686
It's me.

479
00:17:18,686 --> 00:17:19,787
- Yumi.
- Yeah.

480
00:17:19,787 --> 00:17:21,927
- You got my sweater?
- Oh, right.

481
00:17:21,927 --> 00:17:23,526
Hold on, I'll grab the clothes.

482
00:17:23,526 --> 00:17:26,030
Why's Woo Shik's stuff with Yumi?

483
00:17:26,030 --> 00:17:26,928
[Last night]

484
00:17:26,928 --> 00:17:30,374
Run our stuff through the Styler.

485
00:17:30,976 --> 00:17:33,760
[A Styler in Yumi's room
the crew didn't even know about...]

486
00:17:33,760 --> 00:17:35,927
- Tomorrow works, right?
- Yeah.

487
00:17:35,927 --> 00:17:37,709
This place might be
the only spot with a Styler today...

488
00:17:37,709 --> 00:17:41,319
- Right.
- Let me run mine through first.

489
00:17:41,319 --> 00:17:46,691
[Stayed up late running her stuff
and the boys' through the Styler]

490
00:17:48,026 --> 00:17:50,163
Came out nice.

491
00:17:50,163 --> 00:17:53,539
This room's the only one with a Styler.

492
00:17:55,426 --> 00:17:57,245
- Right.
- Got the clothes.

493
00:17:57,245 --> 00:17:58,937
Did you bring my sweater?

494
00:17:58,937 --> 00:18:00,245
Yeah, delivery's here.

495
00:18:00,245 --> 00:18:01,339
My coat too?

496
00:18:01,339 --> 00:18:04,059
Yeah, the delivery's in.

497
00:18:04,059 --> 00:18:05,110
Hi.

498
00:18:05,110 --> 00:18:06,264
[Come on in]

499
00:18:06,264 --> 00:18:07,668
Sleep alright?

500
00:18:07,668 --> 00:18:09,326
So thinking about it,

501
00:18:09,326 --> 00:18:11,126
with no phones, there's no alarm.

502
00:18:11,126 --> 00:18:12,948
- Oh, you guys too?
- Yeah.

503
00:18:12,948 --> 00:18:15,126
So I woke up five times because of it.

504
00:18:15,126 --> 00:18:18,088
Every time he woke up, so did I.

505
00:18:18,088 --> 00:18:19,860
Same clothes as yesterday.

506
00:18:19,860 --> 00:18:21,393
It's a tiny bit different.

507
00:18:21,393 --> 00:18:22,995
More vintage than yesterday.

508
00:18:22,995 --> 00:18:24,908
[One more day of wear added]
A day's worth of vintage.

509
00:18:24,908 --> 00:18:26,885
PD Yun Jin?

510
00:18:26,885 --> 00:18:28,589
- Yu Jin.
- PD Yu Jin?

511
00:18:28,589 --> 00:18:30,837
She acted well.

512
00:18:33,059 --> 00:18:34,159
Seriously.

513
00:18:34,159 --> 00:18:35,440
Oh, you caught the live.

514
00:18:35,440 --> 00:18:37,798
