762
00:27:32,677 --> 00:27:34,641
Is the fare flat for this?

763
00:27:34,641 --> 00:27:36,802
All zones... flat rate?

764
00:27:36,802 --> 00:27:38,182
- For real?
- Yeah.

765
00:27:38,182 --> 00:27:39,584
[Flat fare across all zones]

766
00:27:39,584 --> 00:27:40,618
[Three standard tickets, 5,100 won]

767
00:27:40,618 --> 00:27:41,986
[Expense log, subway tickets, -5,100 won,
balance: 257,450 won]

768
00:27:41,986 --> 00:27:44,226
- Issuing in progress.
- That's awesome.

769
00:27:44,226 --> 00:27:47,158
- Flat fare for all zones...
- Every zone runs the same fare.

770
00:27:47,158 --> 00:27:49,393
[A win for the trio with a long ride]

771
00:27:50,461 --> 00:27:52,752
- It's cute, right?
- So cute.

772
00:27:52,752 --> 00:27:54,892
This should be right.

773
00:27:54,892 --> 00:27:55,993
Let's go!

774
00:27:55,993 --> 00:27:57,435
Shall we head down?

775
00:27:57,435 --> 00:27:59,612
[Camcorder comes out meanwhile]

776
00:27:59,612 --> 00:28:01,939
[Beep]
Looks like we should tap it right here.

777
00:28:01,939 --> 00:28:04,642
[Tapping the reader like a pro]

778
00:28:04,642 --> 00:28:07,393
[Recording Seo Jun and Yumi]

779
00:28:07,393 --> 00:28:09,768
- Hey, guys.
- Yeah.

780
00:28:09,768 --> 00:28:11,208
Where are we headed right now?

781
00:28:11,208 --> 00:28:14,152
- Heading to Namwon.
- Namwon.

782
00:28:14,152 --> 00:28:17,121
[Okay, cut!]

783
00:28:17,121 --> 00:28:18,793
- Hello.
- Hello.

784
00:28:18,793 --> 00:28:20,625
- Did you catch Number One?
- Yes.

785
00:28:20,625 --> 00:28:22,108
- You've seen it?
- I went to the stage greeting!

786
00:28:22,108 --> 00:28:23,396
Really?

787
00:28:23,396 --> 00:28:24,660
Are you on your way to a stage greeting?

788
00:28:24,660 --> 00:28:27,832
No, we're heading off on a trip right now.

789
00:28:27,832 --> 00:28:29,600
You came to the stage greeting
alone that time, right?

790
00:28:29,600 --> 00:28:30,936
Yeah. No way!

791
00:28:30,936 --> 00:28:34,272
- We took a photo together, right?
- No.

792
00:28:34,272 --> 00:28:35,693
[Recognition attempt flopped]

793
00:28:35,693 --> 00:28:37,877
- Then snap one now.
- Could we take one now?

794
00:28:37,877 --> 00:28:39,644
- He came to the stage event.
- Thanks so much.

795
00:28:39,644 --> 00:28:41,045
[While taking a photo with a citizen]

796
00:28:41,045 --> 00:28:44,549
[Line 1 train pulling in]

797
00:28:44,549 --> 00:28:46,065
It's been a while.

798
00:28:46,065 --> 00:28:47,285
Hey, pull it out.

799
00:28:47,285 --> 00:28:48,886
Hold on.

800
00:28:50,054 --> 00:28:52,080
[Showing off the token]

801
00:28:52,080 --> 00:28:53,326
While we've got phones,

802
00:28:53,326 --> 00:28:55,186
- let's snap a bunch of photos together.
- Sure.

803
00:28:55,186 --> 00:28:57,126
- Let's take a ton in Namwon today.
- Yeah.

804
00:28:57,126 --> 00:28:59,096
I'll snap some at Gwanghallu.

805
00:28:59,096 --> 00:29:01,092
- On Ojakgyo Bridge.
- With the phone?

806
00:29:01,092 --> 00:29:02,092
Yeah.

807
00:29:02,092 --> 00:29:04,696
- Are we here?
- Yeah.

808
00:29:04,696 --> 00:29:06,176
[11 stops left...]
- Is this right? - Yeah.

809
00:29:06,176 --> 00:29:07,696
Sitting down's the move.

810
00:29:07,696 --> 00:29:09,807
I'll grab a seat if one opens up.

811
00:29:09,807 --> 00:29:12,043
We have a long way to go.

812
00:29:12,043 --> 00:29:13,959
[At least the bag's got a spot]

813
00:29:13,959 --> 00:29:15,556
[42,200 won worth goes up too]
Let's put it up.

814
00:29:15,556 --> 00:29:17,347
The underwear's in there.

815
00:29:18,149 --> 00:29:21,385
[Empty seat spotted]

816
00:29:21,385 --> 00:29:24,355
[End seat, no less]

817
00:29:24,355 --> 00:29:25,897
- I should...
- Should've grabbed water.

818
00:29:25,897 --> 00:29:27,758
I've got water, want some?

819
00:29:27,758 --> 00:29:29,393
[Rummaging]

820
00:29:29,393 --> 00:29:31,062
[Come on out, ta-da]
Huh?

821
00:29:31,062 --> 00:29:32,096
[Younger brother first]

822
00:29:32,096 --> 00:29:32,863
[Older brother first]

823
00:29:32,863 --> 00:29:33,698
[Younger brother first]

824
00:29:33,698 --> 00:29:34,326
[Okay]

825
00:29:34,326 --> 00:29:36,526
- Was that in the room?
- Yeah, it's from the room.

826
00:29:36,526 --> 00:29:38,842
I grabbed it at the last minute, just in case.

827
00:29:38,842 --> 00:29:39,837
Knew it.

828
00:29:39,837 --> 00:29:41,073
[Drinking too much]

829
00:29:41,073 --> 00:29:42,348
Hey.

830
00:29:42,348 --> 00:29:43,908
[Water control]
Take just a sip for now.

831
00:29:43,908 --> 00:29:44,712
[Oops]

832
00:29:44,712 --> 00:29:46,193
Drink a little.

833
00:29:46,193 --> 00:29:48,212
Let's mark a line here.

834
00:29:49,626 --> 00:29:53,117
So the bus to the lodging from the terminal,

835
00:29:53,117 --> 00:29:55,242
it runs once an hour, apparently.

836
00:29:55,242 --> 00:29:57,788
The village with the lodging is 18km out.

837
00:29:57,788 --> 00:29:59,383
[That's far...]
Right.

838
00:29:59,383 --> 00:30:02,030
- So it might be better if we get a car today.
- Right.

839
00:30:02,030 --> 00:30:03,601
[The accommodation seems pretty rural...]

840
00:30:03,601 --> 00:30:05,108
Should we rent a car-share right now?

841
00:30:05,108 --> 00:30:07,014
[Rent a car?]
Huh?

842
00:30:07,014 --> 00:30:09,348
Now that we have phones, I'll just look it up.

843
00:30:09,348 --> 00:30:12,701
- A car-share in Namwon sounds good.
- Exactly.

844
00:30:12,701 --> 00:30:14,221
Maybe I should download a car-share app too.

845
00:30:14,221 --> 00:30:15,813
[Yumi leads the search for a car-share]

846
00:30:15,813 --> 00:30:17,942
Yumi, which app is this?

847
00:30:17,942 --> 00:30:19,887
- Is it this one? This one?
- No, the one above.

848
00:30:19,887 --> 00:30:21,333
[Pro user]

849
00:30:21,333 --> 00:30:22,563
Yeah, this is it.

850
00:30:22,563 --> 00:30:24,109
[Already has the app]

851
00:30:24,109 --> 00:30:26,917
Let's at least check the price.

852
00:30:26,917 --> 00:30:30,310
[They search together for quite a while...]

853
00:30:30,310 --> 00:30:31,662
Oh, it's up!

854
00:30:31,662 --> 00:30:32,823
It's 60,000 won. What should we do?

855
00:30:32,823 --> 00:30:34,252
- 60,000 won? Reserve it, reserve it.
- Reserve it, reserve it.

856
00:30:34,252 --> 00:30:35,648
- Should we reserve it?
- Reserve it, reserve it.

857
00:30:35,648 --> 00:30:37,441
- Oh, it's not.
- Huh? What is this?

858
00:30:37,441 --> 00:30:40,509
- Oh, there's a discount. 90,000 won.
- 90,000 won?

859
00:30:40,509 --> 00:30:42,688
[Hold on... from what we've got left...]

860
00:30:42,688 --> 00:30:44,654
But it's discounted to half price.

861
00:30:44,654 --> 00:30:46,048
It's a half-price discount.
Let's go with 90,000 won.

862
00:30:46,048 --> 00:30:47,394
Should we just reserve it? Let's reserve it.

863
00:30:47,394 --> 00:30:48,499
Full coverage!

864
00:30:48,499 --> 00:30:49,874
- 90,000 won?
- Yeah, 90,000 won.

865
00:30:49,874 --> 00:30:51,527
- Reserve it. We need it.
- Let's just reserve it.

866
00:30:51,527 --> 00:30:52,554
- Should we just spend it?
- Yeah.

867
00:30:52,554 --> 00:30:54,320
- We can grab some groceries too.
- Yeah.

868
00:30:54,320 --> 00:30:57,120
Yeah, this is how you use phone benefits.

869
00:30:57,120 --> 00:30:59,506
But this was paid with Yumi's money, right?

870
00:30:59,506 --> 00:31:00,992
Hey, but she has to pay me back.

871
00:31:00,992 --> 00:31:03,106
[Woo Shik, we won't just let it go...]

872
00:31:03,106 --> 00:31:05,523
A Cas*** model is showing up too.

873
00:31:05,523 --> 00:31:08,880
[Fully focused on reserving the car...]

874
00:31:08,880 --> 00:31:11,201
Cas***.

875
00:31:11,201 --> 00:31:14,662
[They've arrived at their destination!]

876
00:31:14,662 --> 00:31:18,555
[But no one realizes...]
From there, at the intercity bus terminal...

877
00:31:18,555 --> 00:31:21,121
The doors are opening.

878
00:31:21,729 --> 00:31:26,222
[And people start getting off...]

879
00:31:26,222 --> 00:31:28,635
[Glance]

880
00:31:28,635 --> 00:31:31,054
Oh, we need to get off.

881
00:31:31,054 --> 00:31:33,720
Oh, we need to get off.

882
00:31:34,474 --> 00:31:36,908
- This...
- Get off, get off!

883
00:31:36,908 --> 00:31:39,724
[Even in the chaos,
they carefully grab the shopping bag...]

884
00:31:39,724 --> 00:31:42,106
[Thankfully, they manage to get off...]
Oh, we almost missed our stop.

885
00:31:42,106 --> 00:31:44,068
You didn't tell us on purpose, did you?

886
00:31:44,068 --> 00:31:45,871
You didn't tell us on purpose, did you?

887
00:31:45,871 --> 00:31:48,766
[Almost had them...]
Oh, we were busy renting the car-share...

888
00:31:48,766 --> 00:31:49,859
[They almost missed their stop...]

889
00:31:49,859 --> 00:31:51,865
I was wondering why you weren't
getting off, so I came over...

890
00:31:51,865 --> 00:31:53,619
[Jeez]

891
00:31:53,619 --> 00:31:55,129
Hey, give me all your phones.

892
00:31:55,129 --> 00:31:56,302
- No, we...
- Hand them over now.

893
00:31:56,302 --> 00:31:57,352
[Careful, the homeroom teacher is here]
No, we...

894
00:31:57,352 --> 00:32:00,839
- See? This is why phones are dangerous.
- Whoa...

895
00:32:00,839 --> 00:32:01,879
Whoa...

896
00:32:01,879 --> 00:32:04,360
[Still gives him chills]
- Whoa. - Whoa...

897
00:32:04,360 --> 00:32:07,351
Oh, there's an error again.
I'll try again on the bus.

898
00:32:07,351 --> 00:32:10,447
[Let's try reserving the car
again on the bus...]

899
00:32:10,447 --> 00:32:11,589
[Pause]

900
00:32:11,589 --> 00:32:13,307
There's Gwanmun Market.

901
00:32:13,307 --> 00:32:16,787
Should we grab lunch at Gwanmun Market?

902
00:32:16,787 --> 00:32:18,714
[Seems like no one heard him...]

903
00:32:18,714 --> 00:32:20,428
Should we grab lunch at Gwanmun Market?

904
00:32:20,428 --> 00:32:22,461
Is anyone even listening to Woo Shik?

905
00:32:22,461 --> 00:32:24,647
Let's buy tickets first.

906
00:32:24,647 --> 00:32:26,466
- Should we buy tickets first?
- Ah...

907
00:32:26,466 --> 00:32:27,947
[Immediately agrees]

908
00:32:27,947 --> 00:32:31,021
- Wow!
- There it is.

909
00:32:31,021 --> 00:32:32,227
- Tickets first.
- This way.

910
00:32:32,227 --> 00:32:33,668
[As soon as they exit the subway station]

911
00:32:33,668 --> 00:32:36,147
[Make a U-turn and you'll see it]

912
00:32:36,147 --> 00:32:38,498
[Daegu Seobu Terminal]
Seobu Bus Terminal!

913
00:32:38,498 --> 00:32:40,560
Wait a second!

914
00:32:43,204 --> 00:32:44,857
Wait a second!

915
00:32:44,857 --> 00:32:45,890
Wait a second.

916
00:32:45,890 --> 00:32:47,111
[Director Choi returns]

917
00:32:47,111 --> 00:32:48,250
Okay!

918
00:32:48,250 --> 00:32:53,952
[Title: Seobu Bus Terminal,
below that, two tourists are waving]

919
00:32:54,735 --> 00:32:56,760
Nice vibe!

920
00:32:57,923 --> 00:33:02,159
[Shall we head into this charming terminal?]

921
00:33:02,159 --> 00:33:04,233
[11:04 AM, Daegu Seobu Terminal]
Wow, walnuts!

922
00:33:04,233 --> 00:33:05,907
Those look delicious.

923
00:33:05,907 --> 00:33:07,726
[First, reserve the bus tickets]

924
00:33:07,726 --> 00:33:09,587
Um...

925
00:33:09,587 --> 00:33:11,587
- Namwon, 12 o'clock.
- There is... yeah.

926
00:33:11,587 --> 00:33:13,880
Ours stops at Geochang and Hamyang.

927
00:33:13,880 --> 00:33:15,241
Which time should we get?

928
00:33:15,241 --> 00:33:17,681
[The 12:28 regular bus makes stops]
- 12:28. - Oh.

929
00:33:17,681 --> 00:33:21,068
[The 11:37 deluxe bus is direct]

930
00:33:21,068 --> 00:33:23,884
Oh, the deluxe doesn't make stops.

931
00:33:23,884 --> 00:33:26,508
- Must be because it doesn't stop.
- Yeah, that's why it's faster.

932
00:33:26,508 --> 00:33:27,808
Let's take the deluxe.

933
00:33:27,808 --> 00:33:29,203
- The deluxe has already left!
- Yeah?

934
00:33:29,203 --> 00:33:32,060
- Huh? Wait, 11:30...
- Should we get on it?

935
00:33:32,060 --> 00:33:34,180
- We can get on in 30 minutes!
- Let's take it.

936
00:33:34,180 --> 00:33:36,116
But it costs 10,000 won more.

937
00:33:36,116 --> 00:33:38,675
- So that's a 30,000 won difference?
- It's 10,000 won split among the three of us!

938
00:33:38,675 --> 00:33:41,618
Oh, really? Then let's take the deluxe!

939
00:33:41,618 --> 00:33:43,371
Wow, we're really splurging like this?

940
00:33:43,371 --> 00:33:45,406
- Because we'll have to take another bus...
- Three of us...

941
00:33:45,406 --> 00:33:46,747
But it does save time!

942
00:33:46,747 --> 00:33:47,834
- It does save time.
- Yeah, let's go!

943
00:33:47,834 --> 00:33:49,853
- Let's take the deluxe, then!
- Yeah, let's take it.

944
00:33:49,853 --> 00:33:53,138
- Deluxe, deluxe.
- Three tickets for the 11:37 bus to Namwon!

945
00:33:53,138 --> 00:33:54,340
- Deluxe.
- For three?

946
00:33:54,340 --> 00:33:55,779
- Yes.
- Yes.

947
00:33:55,779 --> 00:33:57,186
Where would you like your seats?

948
00:33:57,186 --> 00:33:58,191
- Might be a bit tight.
- The very back, please.

949
00:33:58,191 --> 00:33:59,797
- The very back?
- The very back, yes.

950
00:33:59,797 --> 00:34:01,137
Are there many seats left besides these three?

951
00:34:01,137 --> 00:34:02,166
There are plenty.

952
00:34:02,166 --> 00:34:04,799
- Everything except the colored ones...
- There are 23 seats left right now.

953
00:34:04,799 --> 00:34:07,780
- Oh, really?
- You can shoot us from seat 24.

954
00:34:07,780 --> 00:34:08,807
[Director Choi even assigns the filming spot]

955
00:34:08,807 --> 00:34:09,988
Our...

956
00:34:09,988 --> 00:34:11,909
It's 42,900 won.

957
00:34:11,909 --> 00:34:14,001
[Expenses: - 42,900 won / Balance: 214,560 won]
That's fine. That's fine.

958
00:34:14,001 --> 00:34:15,060
That's fine. That's fine.

959
00:34:15,060 --> 00:34:18,600
[Ticket purchase complete]
- Let's take a picture of this too! - Okay.

960
00:34:18,600 --> 00:34:20,425
[Look here]

961
00:34:26,441 --> 00:34:28,114
[Now they just need to grab lunch
in the remaining 30 minutes]

962
00:34:28,114 --> 00:34:29,554
So...

963
00:34:29,554 --> 00:34:31,391
- What should we do?
- Wanna grab something at a convenience store?

964
00:34:31,391 --> 00:34:33,287
- Yeah, let's eat at the convenience store!
- Should we eat there?

965
00:34:33,287 --> 00:34:34,401
[To save money,
they head to a convenience store]

966
00:34:34,401 --> 00:34:36,604
Let's just grab some ramyeon.

967
00:34:36,604 --> 00:34:38,536
[11:10 AM, Convenience store]

968
00:34:38,536 --> 00:34:40,198
I'll get something else.

969
00:34:40,198 --> 00:34:41,761
Tempura udon is good too.

970
00:34:41,761 --> 00:34:42,814
But...

971
00:34:42,814 --> 00:34:45,223
- I'll choose this one.
- Hello.

972
00:34:45,223 --> 00:34:48,096
[Both go for the same ramyeon]
Oh okay, I'll have this cup noodles too.

973
00:34:48,096 --> 00:34:49,284
What are you getting?

974
00:34:49,284 --> 00:34:52,452
Then grab me some gummy worms.

975
00:34:52,452 --> 00:34:54,553
You're having gummies for lunch?

976
00:34:54,553 --> 00:34:55,935
Yeah, I can't eat ramyeon right now.

977
00:34:55,935 --> 00:34:57,377
[Po-po's unique taste...]

978
00:34:57,377 --> 00:34:59,419
- Are you really okay with that?
- Yeah.

979
00:34:59,419 --> 00:35:00,739
[Expenses: 2 cup noodles, 1 gummy candy
- 3,200 won / Balance: 211,360 won]

980
00:35:00,739 --> 00:35:02,205
Thank you!

981
00:35:02,205 --> 00:35:04,483
Oh! I should've gotten a granola bar.

982
00:35:04,483 --> 00:35:06,465
[Now she spots an energy bar]
Get a granola bar.

983
00:35:06,465 --> 00:35:08,287
Just 1,200 won...

984
00:35:08,287 --> 00:35:10,293
1,200 won.

985
00:35:10,293 --> 00:35:13,512
[Po-po is getting allowance at 44]

986
00:35:15,679 --> 00:35:18,090
[Meanwhile, the cup noodles are cooking nicely]

987
00:35:21,476 --> 00:35:24,048
[Excited]

988
00:35:24,048 --> 00:35:25,968
Oh, I won't refund it. I'll just buy this.

989
00:35:25,968 --> 00:35:27,165
- Okay.
- Yeah.

990
00:35:27,165 --> 00:35:30,041
[Emergency gummy stash]
In case of an emergency...

991
00:35:30,041 --> 00:35:31,913
- Do you want a bite each?
- No, you have it.

992
00:35:31,913 --> 00:35:34,046
[The trio that even shares a single bean]

993
00:35:34,975 --> 00:35:36,955
[Yum]

994
00:35:36,955 --> 00:35:39,135
It's so good.

995
00:35:40,006 --> 00:35:42,868
- Wow, 40g of protein...
- Does that make sense?

996
00:35:42,868 --> 00:35:44,585
- No way!
- Oh, it's 6g.

997
00:35:44,585 --> 00:35:47,904
[Almost bulked up big time...]
Whoa, that surprised me. Maybe later...

998
00:35:48,954 --> 00:35:51,542
This comes out way better than that.

999
00:35:51,542 --> 00:35:55,169
[Camcorder lover Director Choi]

1000
00:35:56,915 --> 00:35:58,763
What time is it now, by the way?

1001
00:35:58,763 --> 00:36:00,647
I was just thinking the same...

1002
00:36:00,647 --> 00:36:01,871
- Hurry up and eat, you guys.
- 27...

1003
00:36:01,871 --> 00:36:03,284
- Wait, 17 minutes.
- 20 minutes left.

1004
00:36:03,284 --> 00:36:05,034
Yeah, let's eat quickly.

1005
00:36:05,034 --> 00:36:06,305
Careful, careful.

1006
00:36:06,305 --> 00:36:07,693
Yumi, do you want some broth at least?

1007
00:36:07,693 --> 00:36:09,602
[Enjoy your meal]

1008
00:36:09,602 --> 00:36:13,029
[Then we'll enjoy the meal]

1009
00:36:13,029 --> 00:36:15,296
[Blowing]

1010
00:36:23,801 --> 00:36:26,644
[Gotta have some hot broth]

1011
00:36:29,352 --> 00:36:32,612
[Meanwhile, Seo Jun finally
takes his first bite]

1012
00:36:33,684 --> 00:36:36,984
[Devouring it]

1013
00:36:39,526 --> 00:36:43,173
[Happiness really isn't much...]

1014
00:36:46,512 --> 00:36:49,507
[After finishing a simple lunch...]

1015
00:36:49,507 --> 00:36:51,145
[Finally, time to get on the bus]
Namwon.

1016
00:36:51,145 --> 00:36:53,776
Direct to Namwon. Huh?

1017
00:36:54,499 --> 00:36:56,688
[The bus isn't here?]

1018
00:36:56,688 --> 00:36:58,560
Oh, is it this one?

1019
00:36:58,560 --> 00:37:00,074
[Check the ticket...]

1020
00:37:00,074 --> 00:37:01,133
What number is it?

1021
00:37:01,133 --> 00:37:02,452
- Number 6.
- 6?

1022
00:37:02,452 --> 00:37:03,653
[They rush the wrong way without hesitation]

1023
00:37:03,653 --> 00:37:05,306
But this is platform 8?

1024
00:37:05,306 --> 00:37:07,075
[Emergency U-turn, spinning around]
This is 6! Oh...

1025
00:37:07,075 --> 00:37:08,485
It's not here yet.

1026
00:37:08,485 --> 00:37:10,720
Let's sit here.

1027
00:37:10,720 --> 00:37:14,330
[Director Park holding a camcorder again
after a long time]

1028
00:37:15,200 --> 00:37:18,440
- Where are you heading?
- We're... going to Namwon.

1029
00:37:18,440 --> 00:37:19,697
[Can't hear you]
Where?

1030
00:37:19,697 --> 00:37:21,279
Namwon.

1031
00:37:21,279 --> 00:37:23,425
[Okay, got it]
Namwon!

1032
00:37:23,425 --> 00:37:25,724
Hey, when you smile,
a "smile" indicator pops up.

1033
00:37:25,724 --> 00:37:26,792
What do you mean?

1034
00:37:26,792 --> 00:37:29,445
[Newly discovered emotion intensity tracker]
Like, it shows "Smile 20%" and stuff.

1035
00:37:30,809 --> 00:37:32,732
Like this...

1036
00:37:32,732 --> 00:37:33,839
[Stretch it wide]

1037
00:37:33,839 --> 00:37:36,716
100%. Smile 100%.

1038
00:37:36,716 --> 00:37:39,252
- Seo Jun, I'll try doing 35% smile.
- Okay.

1039
00:37:39,252 --> 00:37:41,092
[Ready]

1040
00:37:41,719 --> 00:37:42,839
41%.

1041
00:37:42,839 --> 00:37:44,814
[6% stronger than intended]

1042
00:37:44,814 --> 00:37:47,085
[Adjusting the corners of the mouth]

1043
00:37:47,085 --> 00:37:48,365
42%.

1044
00:37:48,365 --> 00:37:49,851
[Failed]

1045
00:37:49,851 --> 00:37:50,910
35%.

1046
00:37:50,910 --> 00:37:54,578
[While laughing and chatting, the bus arrives]

1047
00:37:54,578 --> 00:37:56,350
It's here!

1048
00:37:56,350 --> 00:37:58,667
- Hello!
- Hello.

1049
00:37:58,667 --> 00:38:00,590
Three people.

1050
00:38:01,872 --> 00:38:03,609
[Even capturing the boarding moment]
Hello.

1051
00:38:03,609 --> 00:38:05,207
Oh, nice vibe.

1052
00:38:05,207 --> 00:38:07,098
Here!

1053
00:38:07,733 --> 00:38:10,251
Oh, dear. This is tough.

1054
00:38:10,251 --> 00:38:12,609
[They put down their heavy bags and sit]

1055
00:38:12,609 --> 00:38:14,759
Should we check the car-share again?

1056
00:38:14,759 --> 00:38:17,115
[Seo Jun registering his driver's license]

1057
00:38:17,115 --> 00:38:18,677
You look handsome.

1058
00:38:18,677 --> 00:38:20,492
[Admiring the driver's license photo]
Let's see. Oh, that came out well.

1059
00:38:20,492 --> 00:38:22,094
You look handsome.

1060
00:38:22,094 --> 00:38:24,176
Very handsome!

1061
00:38:24,176 --> 00:38:28,006
- Wait, Class 1 regular and Class 2 motorcycle?
- We both...

1062
00:38:28,006 --> 00:38:29,947
Are you kidding me?

1063
00:38:29,947 --> 00:38:33,366
[Fumbling around]

1064
00:38:33,366 --> 00:38:34,843
[Look at my photo]

1065
00:38:34,843 --> 00:38:37,123
[Laughing]

1066
00:38:37,123 --> 00:38:40,574
[Finished registration with teasing and praise]
Why do you look like that in your photo?

1067
00:38:40,574 --> 00:38:43,822
Hey, we can rent one at 5:40 today.

1068
00:38:43,822 --> 00:38:46,104
- What?
- A car-share.

1069
00:38:46,104 --> 00:38:48,364
That's 90,000 won, right?

1070
00:38:49,074 --> 00:38:50,270
Huh?

1071
00:38:50,270 --> 00:38:51,597
[Wait...]

1072
00:38:51,597 --> 00:38:53,190
Hey, it's 29,900 won!

1073
00:38:53,190 --> 00:38:55,146
[All eyes on the one-third price]
- What? - 29,900 won!

1074
00:38:55,146 --> 00:38:56,260
- Is that for today?
- Yeah.

1075
00:38:56,260 --> 00:38:59,374
- No, that's...
- No, there's a minus coupon.

1076
00:38:59,374 --> 00:39:01,106
[Confused by the unbelievable price]
Try that. Scroll down.

1077
00:39:01,106 --> 00:39:02,451
No, scroll up.

1078
00:39:02,451 --> 00:39:04,446
Is insurance included?

1079
00:39:04,446 --> 00:39:06,704
Basic coverage is free.

1080
00:39:06,704 --> 00:39:08,338
- Try it.
- Try it quickly.

1081
00:39:08,338 --> 00:39:10,576
- Should we just book it?
- But this starts at 5:40.

1082
00:39:10,576 --> 00:39:12,109
- Pretty good price.
- 5:20...

1083
00:39:12,109 --> 00:39:14,762
[Younger one also agrees]
- Yeah, good. Reserve it. - Wait...

1084
00:39:14,762 --> 00:39:17,790
- Then we'll just kill time until then...
- Go to the park, and...

1085
00:39:17,790 --> 00:39:19,411
- And do some groceries?
- Yeah.

1086
00:39:19,411 --> 00:39:21,214
[Smile intensity 100%]
What car is it?

1087
00:39:21,214 --> 00:39:25,753
K5 booked for 29,900 won.
And we'll pick it up at the terminal.

1088
00:39:25,753 --> 00:39:26,794
Don't lie, you guys.

1089
00:39:26,794 --> 00:39:28,847
[Innocent eyes]
- It's real. - It's real.

1090
00:39:28,847 --> 00:39:30,693
How do you even discount 90,000 won?

1091
00:39:30,693 --> 00:39:32,740
[It's real]

1092
00:39:32,740 --> 00:39:34,714
How many coupons have you been collecting?

1093
00:39:34,714 --> 00:39:36,551
- No, he just...
- I registered for the first time today.

1094
00:39:36,551 --> 00:39:38,573
Oh, maybe there's a benefit
for first-time registration.

1095
00:39:38,573 --> 00:39:40,825
[An unbelievable 75% discount]
- Exactly. - This is not a lie, right?

1096
00:39:40,825 --> 00:39:42,384
I'll give you 29,900 won.

1097
00:39:42,384 --> 00:39:43,886
No way, a car rental this cheap?

1098
00:39:43,886 --> 00:39:45,697
Here, 30,000 won.

1099
00:39:46,718 --> 00:39:48,486
Give me 100 won later, okay?

1100
00:39:48,486 --> 00:39:50,660
Awesome!

1101
00:39:50,660 --> 00:39:53,480
[(Co.) Seobu Terminal]
[After reserving the car to use in Namwon]

1102
00:39:53,480 --> 00:39:56,666
[Finally, the bus to Namwon departs]

1103
00:39:56,666 --> 00:39:58,918
[Departing Daegu Seobu Terminal,
arriving in Namwon / Approx. 1 hour 30 minutes]

1104
00:39:58,918 --> 00:39:59,952
[Wallet appears]

1105
00:39:59,952 --> 00:40:02,796
Let's check the balance first.

1106
00:40:02,796 --> 00:40:06,240
[The treasurer Park's time returns]
One, two, three, four...

1107
00:40:06,240 --> 00:40:08,842
[Never-ending]

1108
00:40:10,195 --> 00:40:11,268
180,000 won.

1109
00:40:11,268 --> 00:40:14,280
[Expense: -29,900 won / Balance: 180,250 won]
That already includes the car-share rental fee.

1110
00:40:14,280 --> 00:40:16,393
Wow, we can eat some pork belly.

1111
00:40:16,393 --> 00:40:18,110
- Wow.
- Oh.

1112
00:40:18,110 --> 00:40:20,840
[And then a message arrives for Seo Jun]
Yeah, I'll see on the way.

1113
00:40:21,613 --> 00:40:23,413
Hey, I've got some good news.

1114
00:40:23,413 --> 00:40:25,974
What? He said there's kimchi in the fridge,
so we can eat it all.

1115
00:40:25,974 --> 00:40:27,819
[Yay]

1116
00:40:27,819 --> 00:40:29,756
Then we just need instant rice.

1117
00:40:29,756 --> 00:40:31,991
[Meal sorted]

1118
00:40:31,991 --> 00:40:34,489
Should I give you some allowance today?

1119
00:40:34,489 --> 00:40:36,555
[Hahaha]

1120
00:40:36,555 --> 00:40:38,156
[Feeling generous]

1121
00:40:38,156 --> 00:40:40,636
Oh no, what are we going to do?
Isn't this dramatic enough?

1122
00:40:40,636 --> 00:40:42,841
We've been living too well.

1123
00:40:42,841 --> 00:40:44,622
What should we do?

1124
00:40:44,622 --> 00:40:46,390
Will every day be like this?

1125
00:40:46,390 --> 00:40:48,630
Let's enjoy it while we can.

1126
00:40:49,494 --> 00:40:51,362
Wait, is the Ojakgyo Bridge in Namwon?

1127
00:40:51,362 --> 00:40:54,063
- Yeah, it's at Gwanghallu.
- Shouldn't we go check out Ojakgyo Bridge?

1128
00:40:54,063 --> 00:40:56,469
It's inside Gwanghallu Garden.

1129
00:40:56,469 --> 00:40:59,480
They say if you register
as a Namwon Nuri Citizen,

1130
00:40:59,480 --> 00:41:01,026
the entrance fee is free.

1131
00:41:01,026 --> 00:41:02,061
How do you even find...

1132
00:41:02,061 --> 00:41:03,475
[Staff: How do you even
find this stuff so well? ]

1133
00:41:03,475 --> 00:41:05,691
Should we try registering
as Namwon Nuri Citizens?

1134
00:41:05,691 --> 00:41:09,508
[Namwon Nuri Citizen system: Register to get
discounts at tourist spots and partner stores]

1135
00:41:09,508 --> 00:41:11,933
Accessing "Dodream Namwon." Wait...

1136
00:41:11,933 --> 00:41:13,952
[Logging into Namwon portal in the dark]

1137
00:41:13,952 --> 00:41:16,015
Seo Jun, are you downloading the app?

1138
00:41:16,015 --> 00:41:18,203
I don't think this is an app.
I'm accessing the website.

1139
00:41:18,203 --> 00:41:19,611
Let me know when you sign up.

1140
00:41:19,611 --> 00:41:22,356
Yeah, I'm trying it right now.

1141
00:41:22,356 --> 00:41:24,195
[Waiting to become Namwon Nuri Citizen]

1142
00:41:24,195 --> 00:41:25,904
[After staring at it forever while signing up]

1143
00:41:25,904 --> 00:41:27,512
Hey, it's done!

1144
00:41:27,512 --> 00:41:30,722
- Are you a Namwon citizen now?
- I just became one.

1145
00:41:30,722 --> 00:41:32,213
[I'm a Namwon Nuri citizen!]

1146
00:41:32,213 --> 00:41:33,492
Wow, restaurants...

1147
00:41:33,492 --> 00:41:34,707
[Park Seo Jun / Namwon Nuri citizen]

1148
00:41:34,707 --> 00:41:35,777
This is a free entry.

1149
00:41:35,777 --> 00:41:37,809
[Gwanghallu Garden: free entry planned]
Just walk in proudly.

1150
00:41:37,809 --> 00:41:39,871
My heart's racing.

1151
00:41:39,871 --> 00:41:41,980
Ta-da!

1152
00:41:41,980 --> 00:41:44,242
[Namwon Nuri citizen #2 is born]

1153
00:41:44,242 --> 00:41:46,513
Is this right?

1154
00:41:46,513 --> 00:41:49,535
[Asking a senior Nuri citizen]
Yeah, go to "My Page."

1155
00:41:49,535 --> 00:41:51,883
You're registered too. Now download it.

1156
00:41:51,883 --> 00:41:54,121
[Secretly proud]
Oh, Choi Woo Shik.

1157
00:41:55,341 --> 00:41:58,543
[Namwon Nuri Citizens #1, #2, #3 are born]
We're all Namwon Nuri Citizens now.

1158
00:41:58,543 --> 00:42:00,411
Should we check out the benefits?

1159
00:42:00,411 --> 00:42:02,235
There are actually a lot.

1160
00:42:02,235 --> 00:42:05,585
At Jeong** Chueotang, one free drink per table.

1161
00:42:05,585 --> 00:42:07,142
Gwang*** Supermarket
200 won off per 10,000 won.

1162
00:42:07,142 --> 00:42:08,790
Geum** Mart 5% off for purchases
over 30,000 won.

1163
00:42:08,790 --> 00:42:10,167
Ri*** Hotel 10% off on payment.

1164
00:42:10,167 --> 00:42:11,997
This is so nice!

1165
00:42:11,997 --> 00:42:13,328
- Right?
- Ta-da!

1166
00:42:13,328 --> 00:42:16,038
You're all set. We're all Namwon Nuri Citizens.

1167
00:42:16,038 --> 00:42:17,141
Nice to meet fellow citizens.

1168
00:42:17,141 --> 00:42:18,688
Nice to meet you, Nuri Citizens.

1169
00:42:18,688 --> 00:42:20,837
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

1170
00:42:20,837 --> 00:42:21,877
Ta-da!

1171
00:42:21,877 --> 00:42:25,037
[Thanks to Seo Jun,
the whole crew is now registered]

1172
00:42:25,037 --> 00:42:28,226
- Alright, let's go to Gwanghallu Garden.
- Yeah.

1173
00:42:28,226 --> 00:42:29,311
Then...

1174
00:42:29,311 --> 00:42:31,117
[Heading straight to Gwanghallu Garden]

1175
00:42:31,117 --> 00:42:34,093
This makes things so much better.
Like knowing how long it takes.

1176
00:42:34,093 --> 00:42:36,782
- While we can use our phones...
- Yeah.

1177
00:42:36,782 --> 00:42:39,305
- how about we plan tomorrow's trip?
- Sounds good.

1178
00:42:39,305 --> 00:42:41,117
[But they take out a paper map first]

1179
00:42:41,117 --> 00:42:43,167
Should we look at the map?

1180
00:42:44,169 --> 00:42:45,492
Let's go wherever you want to go.

1181
00:42:45,492 --> 00:42:47,505
You said you wanted to go to Gongju, right?

1182
00:42:47,505 --> 00:42:49,280
Then for Gongju, we have to go up this way.

1183
00:42:49,280 --> 00:42:51,582
- But Gongju is here?
- Chungcheong-do Province...

1184
00:42:51,582 --> 00:42:52,913
Should we go up?

1185
00:42:52,913 --> 00:42:56,274
He said he wanted Yeonggwang borigulbi,
so I looked it up last night.

1186
00:42:56,274 --> 00:42:57,332
- Yeonggwang?
- Yeah.

1187
00:42:57,332 --> 00:43:01,192
[Three trying to yield to each other]
But it takes like three to four hours by bus.

1188
00:43:01,192 --> 00:43:03,528
Where are we going right now?

1189
00:43:03,528 --> 00:43:04,965
Namwon.

1190
00:43:04,965 --> 00:43:09,758
Then we just need to decide
whether to go north or south.

1191
00:43:09,758 --> 00:43:15,473
I think it'd be nice to stop
somewhere here and then head up.

1192
00:43:15,473 --> 00:43:17,563
That sounds good too.

1193
00:43:18,323 --> 00:43:21,299
Want to go to Jeonju for bibimbap?

1194
00:43:21,299 --> 00:43:24,264
Jeonju bibimbap sounds great.

1195
00:43:24,264 --> 00:43:28,527
- But shouldn't we see the ocean at least once?
- The ocean sounds good too.

1196
00:43:28,527 --> 00:43:30,537
Wouldn't the South Sea
be better than the West Sea?

1197
00:43:30,537 --> 00:43:34,907
It'd be nice to see the South Sea from Boseong.

1198
00:43:34,907 --> 00:43:37,038
- Should we have some green tea in Boseong?
- Yeah, sounds good.

1199
00:43:37,038 --> 00:43:40,564
- From Namwon, we'll go straight...
- Shall we go to Boseong?

1200
00:43:40,564 --> 00:43:42,612
[Unanimously decided: off to Boseong tomorrow]
to Boseong.

1201
00:43:42,612 --> 00:43:45,244
[While they even planned tomorrow]

1202
00:43:45,244 --> 00:43:47,817
[Arrived in Namwon, Jeonbuk Province]
- I'm getting tired. - We're here.

1203
00:43:48,685 --> 00:43:52,358
[Second destination: Namwon]

1204
00:43:52,358 --> 00:43:55,312
[The place where Chunhyang's love blossomed]

1205
00:43:56,072 --> 00:43:59,925
[A place that preserves Korean traditions]

1206
00:43:59,925 --> 00:44:01,917
Do you know how to speak Jeolla-do dialect?

1207
00:44:01,917 --> 00:44:03,622
I don't.

1208
00:44:03,622 --> 00:44:06,578
Namwon style...
Wait, that's Chungcheong-do dialect, right?

1209
00:44:06,578 --> 00:44:09,706
[That's further up north]

1210
00:44:09,706 --> 00:44:11,284
We're in Namwon right now!

1211
00:44:11,284 --> 00:44:14,304
[Jeolla-do dialect patch complete]
Ah, it's Namwon! Yeah, right.

1212
00:44:14,304 --> 00:44:15,860
We're here.

1213
00:44:15,860 --> 00:44:17,623
Wake up.

1214
00:44:17,623 --> 00:44:20,883
[Arrived at Namwon Bus Terminal]
Don't sleep too deeply, wake up!

1215
00:44:21,927 --> 00:44:25,766
[The trio steps outside the terminal]
Why does the air feel so nice? Is it just me?

1216
00:44:27,866 --> 00:44:30,713
Over there, they're selling
giant dumplings. Want some?

1217
00:44:30,713 --> 00:44:34,538
- Are you hungry?
- There are steamed buns over there.

1218
00:44:34,538 --> 00:44:36,747
[The dumpling shop he just spotted]

1219
00:44:36,747 --> 00:44:38,047
Do you want bread?

1220
00:44:38,047 --> 00:44:39,820
Not really, I was just worried
you might be hungry.

1221
00:44:39,820 --> 00:44:45,784
No, I'm okay. Because I'd rather
save room for dinner later.

1222
00:44:45,784 --> 00:44:48,500
And we might eat something
before 5 o'clock anyway, right?

1223
00:44:48,500 --> 00:44:50,585
- Should we go to Gwanghallu Garden then?
- Yeah.

1224
00:44:50,585 --> 00:44:51,923
- Let's take the main road.
- Let's go.

1225
00:44:51,923 --> 00:44:53,283
We just go this way to the main road.

1226
00:44:53,283 --> 00:44:56,205
- Wait a second.
- Wait, let's check the route.

1227
00:44:56,205 --> 00:44:57,265
From here...

1228
00:44:57,265 --> 00:44:58,280
[We have smartphones]

1229
00:44:58,280 --> 00:45:01,340
We should turn here and exit that way.

1230
00:45:01,340 --> 00:45:04,582
[Following leader Po-po]

1231
00:45:04,582 --> 00:45:06,492
Are you looking at the map, Yumi?

1232
00:45:06,492 --> 00:45:09,094
We'll cross at that crosswalk.

1233
00:45:09,094 --> 00:45:10,405
It's written over there.

1234
00:45:10,405 --> 00:45:13,099
- Go there, turn right... then left.
- Yeah.

1235
00:45:13,099 --> 00:45:16,540
[From the terminal to Gwanghallu Garden:
20 minutes on foot]

1236
00:45:16,540 --> 00:45:17,692
Shall we cross here?

1237
00:45:17,692 --> 00:45:19,438
- Let's cross.
- Yeah.

1238
00:45:19,438 --> 00:45:23,482
[Crossing neatly at the crosswalk]

1239
00:45:23,482 --> 00:45:27,514
[The three walk through quiet Namwon streets]

1240
00:45:27,514 --> 00:45:31,997
All the sign names are so cute.
"Clothes repair for a mood boost."

1241
00:45:31,997 --> 00:45:33,398
That's so cute.

1242
00:45:33,398 --> 00:45:35,274
[Warm, friendly signs
all around the neighborhood]

1243
00:45:35,274 --> 00:45:36,374
"Cosmetics!"

1244
00:45:36,374 --> 00:45:38,206
[Honest naming]

1245
00:45:38,206 --> 00:45:40,580
"Let's grab something to eat."

1246
00:45:40,580 --> 00:45:42,362
That gym looks like...

1247
00:45:42,362 --> 00:45:45,603
- it'll really get you in shape.
- Hey...

1248
00:45:45,603 --> 00:45:47,546
