If we didn't have a place,
we would've gone there today.

1482
00:56:00,000 --> 00:56:01,585
Exactly.

1483
00:56:01,585 --> 00:56:02,901
Oh!

1484
00:56:02,901 --> 00:56:05,376
[The two approach excitedly...]

1485
00:56:05,376 --> 00:56:08,017
[Someone already sitting
between Chunhyang and Mong Ryong...]

1486
00:56:08,017 --> 00:56:09,605
Wait.

1487
00:56:12,883 --> 00:56:14,023
[Prefers avant-garde angles]

1488
00:56:14,023 --> 00:56:16,217
Sit lower, lower...

1489
00:56:16,217 --> 00:56:19,550
[Artistic squat shooting mode activated]
Get the feet in frame. Feet in the shot...

1490
00:56:19,550 --> 00:56:20,924
Okay.

1491
00:56:20,924 --> 00:56:22,630
[Laughing]

1492
00:56:22,630 --> 00:56:25,463
[Director Choi is quite pleased with the shot]

1493
00:56:25,463 --> 00:56:27,510
[Satisfied]

1494
00:56:27,510 --> 00:56:30,000
[Model Park is also very satisfied]

1495
00:56:30,000 --> 00:56:32,076
Shouldn't we go left?

1496
00:56:32,076 --> 00:56:35,050
- We have to keep going straight.
- No, just keep going straight.

1497
00:56:35,050 --> 00:56:37,074
[As they try to go straight
following the "human maps"...]

1498
00:56:37,074 --> 00:56:38,910
- Huh?
- Huh?

1499
00:56:40,223 --> 00:56:41,383
What?

1500
00:56:41,383 --> 00:56:43,444
[Music drifting from the alley entrance]

1501
00:56:43,444 --> 00:56:45,628
Let's go there!

1502
00:56:45,628 --> 00:56:47,041
[Woo Shik follows the sound
like he's possessed...]

1503
00:56:47,041 --> 00:56:48,068
Huh?

1504
00:56:48,068 --> 00:56:51,185
[Yumi and Seo Jun follow behind]

1505
00:56:51,185 --> 00:56:54,691
[Glances around...]

1506
00:56:54,691 --> 00:56:57,800
[Then suddenly breaks into a run]

1507
00:56:57,800 --> 00:57:00,393
[Dashing off toward the music]

1508
00:57:00,393 --> 00:57:04,223
[Director Choi snaps out of it
and pulls out the camcorder]

1509
00:57:04,223 --> 00:57:05,309
What is it?

1510
00:57:05,309 --> 00:57:09,662
[They spot a traditional percussion troupe
heading into the alley!]

1511
00:57:09,662 --> 00:57:11,877
[Yumi and Seo Jun, who were following...]

1512
00:57:11,877 --> 00:57:14,044
[Start vibing]

1513
00:57:14,044 --> 00:57:16,117
[Immediately get carried away
by the excitement]

1514
00:57:16,117 --> 00:57:19,288
- What are they doing?
- Let's follow them!

1515
00:57:19,288 --> 00:57:22,840
[He's already following though...]

1516
00:57:22,840 --> 00:57:24,259
- Hello.
- Yes, hello!

1517
00:57:24,259 --> 00:57:25,510
What are they doing?

1518
00:57:25,510 --> 00:57:28,468
- It's Jisinbapgi for Jeongwol Daeboreum!
- Oh!

1519
00:57:28,468 --> 00:57:32,454
[Jisinbapgi: a ritual for peace and protection]
- The 3rd is Jeongwol Daeboreum, right? - Yes.

1520
00:57:32,454 --> 00:57:35,958
[Filmed six days before Daeboreum]
- So they do it in advance before that. - Oh!

1521
00:57:35,958 --> 00:57:39,985
[The two following are amazed
at the unfamiliar sight]

1522
00:57:39,985 --> 00:57:44,553
[Following the resident's guidance,
Woo Shik goes in first]

1523
00:57:44,553 --> 00:57:48,733
[The courtyard is filled
with the percussion troupe]

1524
00:57:48,733 --> 00:57:53,546
[Seo Jun and Yumi also
enter the center of excitement]

1525
00:57:53,546 --> 00:57:57,887
[As the rhythm speeds up...]

1526
00:57:57,887 --> 00:58:01,586
[Their "human drum" energy speeds up too]

1527
00:58:01,586 --> 00:58:03,805
[Excitement synchronized]

1528
00:58:03,805 --> 00:58:06,458
[All of Namwon becomes one in rhythm]

1529
00:58:06,458 --> 00:58:10,362
[Even just their backs look blissful...]

1530
00:58:10,362 --> 00:58:14,292
[The performance reaches its finale...]

1531
00:58:14,292 --> 00:58:18,700
[They wrap up wishing
the elders health and well-being]

1532
00:58:18,700 --> 00:58:22,079
[They exchange final greetings]

1533
00:58:22,079 --> 00:58:25,699
Stay healthy and happy New Year!

1534
00:58:25,699 --> 00:58:27,632
[A whistle of admiration]

1535
00:58:27,632 --> 00:58:28,778
Hehe!

1536
00:58:28,778 --> 00:58:30,244
They're wishing us good health.

1537
00:58:30,244 --> 00:58:32,301
[A thank-you gift from the village: yogurt]

1538
00:58:32,301 --> 00:58:34,555
I think that's what the elders
are doing. For health...

1539
00:58:34,555 --> 00:58:35,941
On Jeongwol Daeboreum...

1540
00:58:35,941 --> 00:58:37,848
- So this is for Jeongwol Daeboreum?
- Oh, yeah.

1541
00:58:37,848 --> 00:58:40,907
They come back every year for this event.

1542
00:58:40,907 --> 00:58:43,554
- They're really famous people!
- They're famous!

1543
00:58:43,554 --> 00:58:46,615
- They're the most famous!
- Oh!

1544
00:58:46,615 --> 00:58:48,908
They're number one in Korea.

1545
00:58:48,908 --> 00:58:49,948
"Number One"...

1546
00:58:49,948 --> 00:58:51,984
[The lead actor of "Number One,"
suddenly overwhelmed with honor]

1547
00:58:51,984 --> 00:58:53,551
Should we take a photo with that troupe?

1548
00:58:53,551 --> 00:58:55,300
Oh, should we take one? Let's take a photo.

1549
00:58:55,300 --> 00:58:57,537
- Hello!
- Hello!

1550
00:58:58,402 --> 00:58:59,508
Hello!

1551
00:58:59,508 --> 00:59:00,888
[About to ask for a photo]

1552
00:59:00,888 --> 00:59:04,379
[The leader suddenly turns around...]

1553
00:59:05,528 --> 00:59:08,613
[Performance resumes]

1554
00:59:08,613 --> 00:59:12,472
[We're doing an encore,
so take as many photos as you want]

1555
00:59:12,472 --> 00:59:16,693
[Basically a private concert for the trio]

1556
00:59:16,693 --> 00:59:19,595
[Audience 1 fully immersed in rhythm]

1557
00:59:19,595 --> 00:59:23,648
[Audience 2 and 3 in total trance]

1558
00:59:23,648 --> 00:59:27,760
[Good fortune spreading everywhere]

1559
00:59:27,760 --> 00:59:33,211
[The rhythm reaches its peak,
and Woo Shik's excitement rises]

1560
00:59:33,211 --> 00:59:36,159
[As the leader revs up the sangmo...]

1561
00:59:36,159 --> 00:59:38,950
[Full-on spinning sangmo in action]

1562
00:59:38,950 --> 00:59:42,326
[As the final gong signals the end]

1563
00:59:42,326 --> 00:59:46,084
[The trio bows their heads in thanks]

1564
00:59:46,084 --> 00:59:48,312
We're supposed to get lucky money.

1565
00:59:48,312 --> 00:59:50,444
- Oh, a big amount?
- Lucky money.

1566
00:59:50,444 --> 00:59:53,344
- Mr. Choi Woo Shik! Oh, nice to meet you.
- Oh, yes.

1567
00:59:53,344 --> 00:59:54,391
But we...

1568
00:59:54,391 --> 00:59:56,368
[How do we tell them our entire budget
is just 150,000 won...]

1569
00:59:56,368 --> 00:59:57,959
[But the treasurer already opened the wallet]

1570
00:59:57,959 --> 01:00:00,843
- Oh, does it open?
- Oh my.

1571
01:00:00,843 --> 01:00:03,226
[Give a small amount as a token of gratitude]
Thank you!

1572
01:00:03,226 --> 01:00:04,760
Thank you!

1573
01:00:04,760 --> 01:00:09,018
[The elders respond
with a full instrumental send-off]

1574
01:00:09,018 --> 01:00:11,096
- Thank you!
- Thank you!

1575
01:00:11,096 --> 01:00:14,149
[They turn back, filled with deep emotion]
- Thank you, thank you! - Yes.

1576
01:00:14,149 --> 01:00:15,604
- Good luck with the filming.
- Oh, thank you!

1577
01:00:15,604 --> 01:00:16,757
Come to Namwon often!

1578
01:00:16,757 --> 01:00:18,040
- Yes!
- Yes!

1579
01:00:18,040 --> 01:00:20,643
- Come to Namwon from time to time!
- Yes, thank you!

1580
01:00:20,643 --> 01:00:21,786
It's the best!

1581
01:00:21,786 --> 01:00:23,588
[Triple thumbs-up farewell]

1582
01:00:23,588 --> 01:00:25,800
- Wait, 10,000 won.
- 10,000 won...

1583
01:00:25,800 --> 01:00:27,742
[Expense: -10,000 won, remaining: 142,250 won]
- 10,000 won. - 10,000 won...

1584
01:00:27,742 --> 01:00:29,852
- Oh, but...
- If it's luck money, it's fine.

1585
01:00:29,852 --> 01:00:33,646
- Good energy will come in.
- Yeah, it'll bring us good luck.

1586
01:00:33,646 --> 01:00:37,017
- But that was so exciting.
- Yeah.

1587
01:00:37,017 --> 01:00:38,382
- Definitely.
- Yeah.

1588
01:00:38,382 --> 01:00:40,852
[The lingering excitement won't fade]
Ding-da-dang-dang...

1589
01:00:40,852 --> 01:00:44,632
- I was just drawn to give 10,000 won.
- Yeah, when I heard the gong, I was just...

1590
01:00:44,632 --> 01:00:46,353
My soul gets sucked in.

1591
01:00:46,353 --> 01:00:47,624
"What is this now?"

1592
01:00:47,624 --> 01:00:50,937
- To wish Egg ** Coming success.
- Yeah, to wish them success.

1593
01:00:50,937 --> 01:00:53,117
I actually like traditional percussion.

1594
01:00:53,117 --> 01:00:55,593
I think I've liked the gong for a long time.

1595
01:00:55,593 --> 01:00:58,035
So I went as soon as I heard it.

1596
01:00:58,035 --> 01:01:00,161
From the back, I actually thought...

1597
01:01:00,161 --> 01:01:02,464
I thought they were younger.

1598
01:01:02,464 --> 01:01:03,997
But when I got there,

1599
01:01:03,997 --> 01:01:07,946
they were all cute grandmas and grandpas.

1600
01:01:07,946 --> 01:01:11,006
[That's why it left a deeper impression]
So it turned into a bit of a fun twist.

1601
01:01:11,006 --> 01:01:14,453
Everyone was so excited,
so it made me excited too!

1602
01:01:14,453 --> 01:01:18,932
I think it would've felt a bit off
if we hadn't given it.

1603
01:01:18,932 --> 01:01:21,852
They even performed one more time for us.

1604
01:01:21,852 --> 01:01:23,572
Yeah...

1605
01:01:23,572 --> 01:01:26,675
But don't let your soul get sucked in again.

1606
01:01:26,675 --> 01:01:28,955
- Wait, what? Ah, the north gate!
- Gwanghallu Garden North Gate!

1607
01:01:28,955 --> 01:01:31,943
[Note: They were originally
heading to Gwanghallu Garden]

1608
01:01:31,943 --> 01:01:34,292
Huh? Are we almost there now?

1609
01:01:34,292 --> 01:01:35,911
- This is the north gate.
- This isn't it.

1610
01:01:35,911 --> 01:01:37,479
No, we need to go a bit further.

1611
01:01:37,479 --> 01:01:39,875
[They decide to go a bit further
to find the ticket booth!]

1612
01:01:39,875 --> 01:01:42,917
But we got
drawn in by the percussion performance.

1613
01:01:42,917 --> 01:01:46,280
- All of a sudden...
- We've basically ended up doing a full loop.

1614
01:01:48,771 --> 01:01:50,422
It'd be pretty at night too.

1615
01:01:50,422 --> 01:01:54,084
I feel like people would
come here a lot at night.

1616
01:01:54,084 --> 01:01:57,736
[Romantic at night]

1617
01:01:57,736 --> 01:02:02,846
[Peaceful in the daytime,
beloved Cheongsachorong Street]

1618
01:02:02,846 --> 01:02:06,276
[Thanks to getting a bit lost,
they end up walking a beautiful path]

1619
01:02:06,276 --> 01:02:07,435
Ah, this helps digestion.

1620
01:02:07,435 --> 01:02:08,779
Same.

1621
01:02:09,552 --> 01:02:10,704
There's the ticket booth!

1622
01:02:10,704 --> 01:02:14,159
"That's right! Finally, they arrive
at the ticket booth!"

1623
01:02:14,859 --> 01:02:16,684
[Passing through a construction road...]

1624
01:02:16,684 --> 01:02:17,993
"That's right!"

1625
01:02:17,993 --> 01:02:21,718
[Finally, they arrive at the ticket booth!]

1626
01:02:21,718 --> 01:02:23,782
Hello!

1627
01:02:23,782 --> 01:02:26,682
- Hello!
- We...

1628
01:02:26,682 --> 01:02:28,712
- Well...
- We have that thing!

1629
01:02:28,712 --> 01:02:32,430
- We...
- "Namwon Nuri Citizens!"

1630
01:02:32,430 --> 01:02:35,713
[Showing off their Namwon Nuri Citizen cards]
Can we just show the card?

1631
01:02:35,713 --> 01:02:38,226
- Everyone, take yours out!
- Oh, yeah.

1632
01:02:38,226 --> 01:02:40,224
[All united in fate for free entry]

1633
01:02:40,224 --> 01:02:42,085
- I'll give you the tickets.
- Alright!

1634
01:02:42,085 --> 01:02:43,352
Should we grab one?

1635
01:02:43,352 --> 01:02:44,445
[4,000 won per person saved, super save]

1636
01:02:44,445 --> 01:02:46,961
Wow! Thank you!

1637
01:02:46,961 --> 01:02:48,793
[Nuri ceremony]

1638
01:02:48,793 --> 01:02:50,163
Thank you!

1639
01:02:50,163 --> 01:02:51,497
Film this, Woo Shik!

1640
01:02:51,497 --> 01:02:53,337
[Standby ready]

1641
01:02:53,337 --> 01:02:54,384
Okay!

1642
01:02:54,384 --> 01:02:56,553
[Enjoying freebies as Nuri citizens]

1643
01:02:56,553 --> 01:02:57,752
- Okay!
- Okay.

1644
01:02:57,752 --> 01:02:59,854
Should I show this here?

1645
01:03:01,204 --> 01:03:02,384
Okay, thank you!

1646
01:03:02,384 --> 01:03:04,089
[The three Nuri citizens enter without issue]

1647
01:03:04,089 --> 01:03:07,305
How is it, entering like this
as Namwon Nuri Citizens?

1648
01:03:07,305 --> 01:03:09,600
- It's nice.
- Seriously, the perks are no joke.

1649
01:03:09,600 --> 01:03:11,673
[So proud]

1650
01:03:11,673 --> 01:03:14,086
- Hey, there's a swing over there!
- Oh, what?

1651
01:03:14,086 --> 01:03:15,111
Where?

1652
01:03:15,111 --> 01:03:16,885
- The swing!
- Let's ride the swing!

1653
01:03:16,885 --> 01:03:17,919
Let's ride the swing.

1654
01:03:17,919 --> 01:03:19,974
Yumi, you should spin 360 degrees on that.

1655
01:03:19,974 --> 01:03:21,552
- No, I'll break a rib doing that.
- We'll push you.

1656
01:03:21,552 --> 01:03:24,835
My ribs will twist, no way.
Then I'll just fall again.

1657
01:03:24,835 --> 01:03:27,157
[Arriving at the swing area]

1658
01:03:27,157 --> 01:03:29,646
Oh my, there are so many kids waiting.

1659
01:03:29,646 --> 01:03:31,632
[More kids than expected...]

1660
01:03:31,632 --> 01:03:33,920
[Standing there awkwardly]

1661
01:03:33,920 --> 01:03:36,686
[Woo Shik bravely leads into the swing zone]

1662
01:03:36,686 --> 01:03:37,711
Hey kids.

1663
01:03:37,711 --> 01:03:40,445
- What are you doing? That's dirty.
- Where does the line start?

1664
01:03:40,445 --> 01:03:41,497
[It's here!]
There?

1665
01:03:41,497 --> 01:03:42,915
You can stand at the end here.

1666
01:03:42,915 --> 01:03:44,184
From here to there?

1667
01:03:44,184 --> 01:03:45,257
[They kindly show where the waiting line is]

1668
01:03:45,257 --> 01:03:48,168
Hey guys! Stop riding the swing and move along.

1669
01:03:48,168 --> 01:03:49,441
Wait, why?

1670
01:03:49,441 --> 01:03:50,519
[Dazed]

1671
01:03:50,519 --> 01:03:51,709
[The kids leave at the teacher's instruction]
We have to go back to our accommodation.

1672
01:03:51,709 --> 01:03:54,449
[Woo Shik left standing there all alone...]

1673
01:03:54,449 --> 01:03:57,859
[Even as they leave,
the kids politely say goodbye]

1674
01:03:57,859 --> 01:04:00,785
[Overwhelmed by the energy,
even Seo Jun looks drained...]

1675
01:04:00,785 --> 01:04:03,178
[Somehow ends up first in line]

1676
01:04:03,178 --> 01:04:05,342
Perfect timing!

1677
01:04:05,342 --> 01:04:07,278
Alright! Hop on.

1678
01:04:07,278 --> 01:04:09,478
[Suddenly overflowing with big-bro energy]

1679
01:04:09,478 --> 01:04:10,489
Let's give it a try.

1680
01:04:10,489 --> 01:04:14,222
[Po-po goes first]
Hey, don't... don't spin me!

1681
01:04:14,222 --> 01:04:15,946
- Ready?
- Yeah!

1682
01:04:15,946 --> 01:04:17,959
[Hehehahaha]

1683
01:04:17,959 --> 01:04:19,944
[Tension at its peak]
Hey!

1684
01:04:19,944 --> 01:04:22,612
Hey, seriously, my ribs...

1685
01:04:22,612 --> 01:04:25,354
Whoa, this feels amazing!

1686
01:04:25,354 --> 01:04:27,230
[Thrilling]

1687
01:04:27,230 --> 01:04:28,842
Hey, it's not moving...

1688
01:04:28,842 --> 01:04:31,722
[Harder to get momentum than expected]
It's not moving... yay!

1689
01:04:31,722 --> 01:04:34,659
- Alright! From the start again!
- Yeah, from the start.

1690
01:04:34,659 --> 01:04:36,907
With this foot... wait!

1691
01:04:36,907 --> 01:04:37,970
[Hold on tight]

1692
01:04:37,970 --> 01:04:40,102
Hey, wait... let go!

1693
01:04:40,102 --> 01:04:41,515
[The younger ones are having
the time of their lives]

1694
01:04:41,515 --> 01:04:43,728
- Let's go!
- No! Don't push!

1695
01:04:43,728 --> 01:04:47,081
[With help from the younger ones,
she swings higher and higher]

1696
01:04:47,081 --> 01:04:49,394
[Now it's Yumi's turn to show strength]

1697
01:04:54,848 --> 01:04:57,238
Push!

1698
01:04:57,238 --> 01:04:59,249
[Excited like a child]

1699
01:04:59,249 --> 01:05:01,636
Hey, you guys should try it too!

1700
01:05:01,636 --> 01:05:02,789
Wow, this is heavy.

1701
01:05:02,789 --> 01:05:04,342
[Second rider: the sporty treasurer Park]

1702
01:05:04,342 --> 01:05:06,480
[Even Treasurer Park wobbles at first]
Should I give you a push at first?

1703
01:05:06,480 --> 01:05:07,531
How do you ride this?

1704
01:05:07,531 --> 01:05:09,820
- I'll push you once.
- Try pushing.

1705
01:05:09,820 --> 01:05:11,113
- Push?
- Yeah.

1706
01:05:11,113 --> 01:05:13,523
- Push?
- Yeah.

1707
01:05:13,523 --> 01:05:15,766
[Not enough]

1708
01:05:15,766 --> 01:05:18,520
- It's not swinging properly.
- It's not swinging right.

1709
01:05:18,520 --> 01:05:21,427
[If it won't swing, I'll make it swing]

1710
01:05:21,427 --> 01:05:24,312
[Thanks to Woo Shik, he gets a taste of thrill]

1711
01:05:26,912 --> 01:05:30,166
- Come here.
- Come here.

1712
01:05:30,166 --> 01:05:31,372
Try standing first.

1713
01:05:31,372 --> 01:05:32,995
[Last up, Woo Shik tries it too]

1714
01:05:32,995 --> 01:05:34,673
Just stand straight.

1715
01:05:34,673 --> 01:05:36,426
[Boards pretty smoothly]

1716
01:05:37,953 --> 01:05:39,577
Not working, right?

1717
01:05:39,577 --> 01:05:42,018
- Nope. You need to push.
- Just once, try pushing from the hips.

1718
01:05:42,018 --> 01:05:43,110
Okay, go.

1719
01:05:43,110 --> 01:05:46,138
[Everyone joins forces to get the swing going]

1720
01:05:47,738 --> 01:05:51,961
[Almost riding it face-first...]

1721
01:05:51,961 --> 01:05:53,456
Want me to push you?

1722
01:05:53,456 --> 01:05:56,035
[Big sister wants to push the youngest]

1723
01:05:56,035 --> 01:05:57,506
Alright!

1724
01:05:57,506 --> 01:05:59,167
Let's go now!

1725
01:05:59,167 --> 01:06:00,408
[Okay]

1726
01:06:04,773 --> 01:06:07,301
[Full-body bow of apology]

1727
01:06:07,301 --> 01:06:09,526
[Embarrassed]

1728
01:06:09,526 --> 01:06:11,731
[The younger ones rush over immediately...]

1729
01:06:11,731 --> 01:06:13,692
[Worried but also funny]

1730
01:06:13,692 --> 01:06:16,913
- Oh no, get up quickly.
- This is embarrassing, get up, quick.

1731
01:06:16,913 --> 01:06:18,909
Wow, the weather's nice!

1732
01:06:18,909 --> 01:06:21,638
[Changing the subject to ease the situation]
- The weather's nice. - Get up quickly.

1733
01:06:21,638 --> 01:06:24,685
- Get up quickly.
- Oh, guess you wanted to see it lying down.

1734
01:06:24,685 --> 01:06:26,074
- Are you okay? Your face?
- I'm fine.

1735
01:06:26,074 --> 01:06:29,146
Please ignore us.

1736
01:06:29,146 --> 01:06:30,270
[Thankfully not injured]

1737
01:06:30,270 --> 01:06:32,414
Wow, the weather's nice, right?

1738
01:06:32,414 --> 01:06:35,014
- You were trying to see the moon, huh?
- Right.

1739
01:06:35,014 --> 01:06:38,060
Oh, shall we go to Gwanghallu now?

1740
01:06:38,847 --> 01:06:41,799
Looks like we got a good shot.

1741
01:06:41,799 --> 01:06:43,472
[Po-po unintentionally creates a great shot...]

1742
01:06:43,472 --> 01:06:45,345
- Alright, sit here for a bit.
- Okay.

1743
01:06:45,345 --> 01:06:47,038
- I'll check for a moment.
- Yeah.

1744
01:06:47,038 --> 01:06:51,302
If it hurt, you'd scream or cry, but instead...

1745
01:06:51,302 --> 01:06:53,520
I just started laughing like crazy.

1746
01:06:53,520 --> 01:06:56,994
But I can't lift my head because...

1747
01:06:56,994 --> 01:07:00,743
I really wanted to push him,
but I got pushed instead...

1748
01:07:00,743 --> 01:07:02,953
[Next thing she knew, she was on the mat]

1749
01:07:02,953 --> 01:07:04,901
Po-po was just...

1750
01:07:04,901 --> 01:07:07,124
she was trying to push me for fun.

1751
01:07:07,124 --> 01:07:09,042
But she ended up falling on herself.

1752
01:07:09,042 --> 01:07:11,769
I did feel a bit sorry.
I also felt kind of bad for her, but...

1753
01:07:11,769 --> 01:07:13,476
[He feels bad, but it's still funny...
can't help it...]

1754
01:07:13,476 --> 01:07:15,868
Ah, I did feel sorry.

1755
01:07:15,868 --> 01:07:18,849
- Let's just go to Ojakgyo Bridge.
- Yeah.

1756
01:07:18,849 --> 01:07:20,323
Let's go to Ojakgyo Bridge.

1757
01:07:20,323 --> 01:07:21,676
[They decide to cross Ojakgyo Bridge
and head to Gwanghallu]

1758
01:07:22,916 --> 01:07:25,388
So many things happened today!

1759
01:07:25,388 --> 01:07:26,984
Feels like it's like this every day.

1760
01:07:26,984 --> 01:07:28,529
Oh, we arrived yesterday, right?

1761
01:07:28,529 --> 01:07:30,062
Oh, but why does it feel like two days?

1762
01:07:30,062 --> 01:07:31,962
- Right.
- Right? I feel the same.

1763
01:07:31,962 --> 01:07:33,642
[Living each day intensely...]

1764
01:07:33,642 --> 01:07:35,652
- Please take a picture of us here too!
- Yeah.

1765
01:07:35,652 --> 01:07:36,883
- Here?
- Yes.

1766
01:07:36,883 --> 01:07:40,097
[Kids are taking cute photos at the photo zone]

1767
01:07:40,097 --> 01:07:42,245
Oh, so cute!

1768
01:07:42,245 --> 01:07:44,019
Let's copy their pose.

1769
01:07:44,019 --> 01:07:46,844
[Ready to copy-paste the pose]
- The pose is cute! - One, two, three!

1770
01:07:46,844 --> 01:07:49,360
- You're so pretty!
- Thanks!

1771
01:07:49,360 --> 01:07:51,949
But I feel like I've seen you somewhere.

1772
01:07:51,949 --> 01:07:54,029
- Our Po-po should be in the middle.
- Yeah.

1773
01:07:54,029 --> 01:07:56,880
[Getting ready to take a photo
with Po-po in the center]

1774
01:07:56,880 --> 01:07:59,182
- Like this?
- Let's just do it like this!

1775
01:08:00,230 --> 01:08:03,328
[Recreating the kids' pose]

1776
01:08:04,403 --> 01:08:05,749
[Laughing]

1777
01:08:05,749 --> 01:08:06,901
Alright, that's good.

1778
01:08:06,901 --> 01:08:08,962
- Good!
- Good!

1779
01:08:08,962 --> 01:08:11,515
[Memories at Gwanghallu Garden]

1780
01:08:11,515 --> 01:08:12,921
Oh my, look at that!

1781
01:08:12,921 --> 01:08:15,461
- That duck looks really cute!
- Right?

1782
01:08:15,461 --> 01:08:18,077
- You know ducks move in groups, right?
- Yeah.

1783
01:08:18,077 --> 01:08:19,740
- Oh, really? Normally?
- Yeah.

1784
01:08:19,740 --> 01:08:21,222
- Yeah, they always move in a bunch.
- Look at that face!

1785
01:08:21,222 --> 01:08:22,758
So cute!

1786
01:08:22,758 --> 01:08:24,064
Is it a mallard?

1787
01:08:24,064 --> 01:08:25,437
[We look like ducks, but we're mandarin ducks]

1788
01:08:25,437 --> 01:08:27,118
Wow, how are they this cute?

1789
01:08:27,118 --> 01:08:29,258
Look at the feet. See the feet?
Aren't they so cute?

1790
01:08:29,258 --> 01:08:30,805
Wow, the feet are so cute!

1791
01:08:30,805 --> 01:08:31,974
[Deadly cute foot moves]

1792
01:08:31,974 --> 01:08:33,372
Hurry, take it!

1793
01:08:33,372 --> 01:08:36,313
[Director Choi begins
the mandarin duck sequence]

1794
01:08:36,313 --> 01:08:37,945
Why is it so fast?

1795
01:08:37,945 --> 01:08:39,493
[I've chosen you as the main character]

1796
01:08:39,493 --> 01:08:41,246
They're all hiding under the trees over there.

1797
01:08:41,246 --> 01:08:43,113
[Thank you so much]

1798
01:08:43,113 --> 01:08:45,673
[After watching absentmindedly for a while]
- Look, the feet. - The feet...

1799
01:08:45,673 --> 01:08:46,770
Oh, my!

1800
01:08:46,770 --> 01:08:47,883
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

1801
01:08:47,883 --> 01:08:50,736
[Heading to cross Ojakgyo Bridge]

1802
01:08:50,736 --> 01:08:53,098
[For Gyeonu and Jingnyeo]

1803
01:08:53,098 --> 01:08:57,920
[The bridge said to be made
by magpies and crows]

1804
01:08:57,920 --> 01:09:00,667
[Crossing the bridge of love]
We can't go to Gwanghallu... huh? We can go up!

1805
01:09:00,667 --> 01:09:02,259
- Oh, you're right.
- Yeah.

1806
01:09:02,259 --> 01:09:05,206
- Should we go up? Yeah.
- Let's sit for a bit.

1807
01:09:07,519 --> 01:09:10,719
[Decide to rest at Gwanghallu!]

1808
01:09:10,719 --> 01:09:13,210
[Take off shoes before entering]

1809
01:09:13,210 --> 01:09:16,527
We'll rest for a bit.

1810
01:09:17,288 --> 01:09:19,321
- Wow, this is nice!
- This is nice!

1811
01:09:19,321 --> 01:09:20,831
[Director Choi immediately
turns on the camcorder]

1812
01:09:20,831 --> 01:09:23,599
- Wow, nice!
- This place is nice!

1813
01:09:23,599 --> 01:09:26,066
Oh dear...

1814
01:09:26,066 --> 01:09:28,439
Woo Shik, take your bag off
and come here for a second.

1815
01:09:28,439 --> 01:09:29,558
Try sitting there!

1816
01:09:29,558 --> 01:09:31,819
[Creative inspiration is going wild today]

1817
01:09:34,077 --> 01:09:36,703
Good! This is perfect!

1818
01:09:37,290 --> 01:09:40,268
[Now passing the baton to Treasurer Park]

1819
01:09:40,268 --> 01:09:41,928
The name of this place is...

1820
01:09:41,928 --> 01:09:44,515
- Gwanghallu?
- Gwanghallu.

1821
01:09:44,515 --> 01:09:46,044
[Strike a pose]

1822
01:09:46,044 --> 01:09:48,664
[I've got to strike a pose
that fits Gwanghallu]

1823
01:09:48,664 --> 01:09:49,826
[Another pose]

1824
01:09:49,826 --> 01:09:51,165
Where is Seo Jun?

1825
01:09:51,165 --> 01:09:52,589
Over there.

1826
01:09:52,589 --> 01:09:55,059
[With a neat, composed smile]

1827
01:09:55,059 --> 01:09:56,914
[Treasurer Park's photoshoot complete]
Ah, it's warm.

1828
01:09:56,914 --> 01:09:59,115
- It's warm. Sit down, sit for a bit.
- Sit here.

1829
01:09:59,115 --> 01:10:00,918
- Sit.
- The floor is warm?

1830
01:10:00,918 --> 01:10:02,111
It's sunlight!

1831
01:10:02,111 --> 01:10:04,852
[The wooden floor warmed perfectly by the sun]

1832
01:10:04,852 --> 01:10:08,138
[About an hour left until car sharing]

1833
01:10:08,138 --> 01:10:10,390
[We've got plenty of time...]

1834
01:10:11,391 --> 01:10:13,943
[Let's lie down first]

1835
01:10:13,943 --> 01:10:16,265
[Po-po also slowly gets ready to lie down...]

1836
01:10:16,265 --> 01:10:19,644
[Everyone powered off]

1837
01:10:19,644 --> 01:10:20,790
[Just as they're about to recharge for a bit]

1838
01:10:20,790 --> 01:10:22,992
Why am I so tired?

1839
01:10:22,992 --> 01:10:24,929
Is it because I'm getting old?

1840
01:10:24,929 --> 01:10:26,971
[Kids come running in loudly]

1841
01:10:26,971 --> 01:10:28,983
Huh?

1842
01:10:28,983 --> 01:10:32,242
[They naturally head toward the back]
Oh, you can't go in there!

1843
01:10:32,242 --> 01:10:34,655
There's a room over there too?

1844
01:10:34,655 --> 01:10:38,526
[What kind of room is it?]

1845
01:10:38,526 --> 01:10:42,126
[Following the direction the kids went]

1846
01:10:42,126 --> 01:10:44,135
[A fairly spacious area]

1847
01:10:44,135 --> 01:10:46,622
Ah, it's connected like this!

1848
01:10:46,622 --> 01:10:47,675
Like this.

1849
01:10:47,675 --> 01:10:49,939
[A "secret room" discovered thanks to the kids]

1850
01:10:49,939 --> 01:10:51,812
Oh, that's not it!

1851
01:10:51,812 --> 01:10:53,557
[Retreating to a nearby spot]

1852
01:10:53,557 --> 01:10:56,010
It's me... please open it.

1853
01:10:56,010 --> 01:10:57,358
Seo Jun, say hello to her.

1854
01:10:57,358 --> 01:10:59,472
- Hello...
- Hi!

1855
01:10:59,472 --> 01:11:01,054
- I'm Park Seo Jun.
- You're Park Seo Jun?

1856
01:11:01,054 --> 01:11:03,218
[You're... Park Seo Jun?]
Come here. Come here for a second.

1857
01:11:03,218 --> 01:11:06,051
Here, this is Seo Jun!

1858
01:11:06,051 --> 01:11:07,698
Your name is Seo Jun?

1859
01:11:07,698 --> 01:11:10,427
He says he's Park Seo Jun. Say hello to him.

1860
01:11:10,427 --> 01:11:12,893
[A deep bow]
- Come here. - Hello!

1861
01:11:12,893 --> 01:11:14,387
Nice to meet you!

1862
01:11:14,387 --> 01:11:16,604
[Nice to meet you, I'm Seo Jun too]
Is he really Park Seo Jun?

1863
01:11:16,604 --> 01:11:20,602
- I named him Seo Jun because of Park Seo Jun.
- Oh my!

1864
01:11:20,602 --> 01:11:22,938
[Then right onto my lap]
Let's take a picture.

1865
01:11:22,938 --> 01:11:24,845
Is Woo Shik not here?

1866
01:11:24,845 --> 01:11:27,194
They say Woo Shik's not here.

1867
01:11:27,194 --> 01:11:29,627
[Here, the same-name duo bonds warmly]

1868
01:11:29,627 --> 01:11:31,580
[Mom moved by meeting her favorites]
Hey, your dad's gonna be so surprised.

1869
01:11:31,580 --> 01:11:32,680
Say your name is Woo Shik.

1870
01:11:32,680 --> 01:11:33,967
[Laughing]

1871
01:11:33,967 --> 01:11:35,793
Say your name is Woo Shik.

1872
01:11:35,793 --> 01:11:38,920
Don't bow. We don't have money.

1873
01:11:38,920 --> 01:11:40,418
[Info: It was a few days
after the Lunar New Year filming day]

1874
01:11:40,418 --> 01:11:41,514
Bye!

1875
01:11:41,514 --> 01:11:43,359
[Baby Seo Jun's saying goodbye]

1876
01:11:43,359 --> 01:11:45,205
Seo Jun, take care!

1877
01:11:45,205 --> 01:11:46,952
- Stay healthy.
- Uncle Park Seo Jun!

1878
01:11:46,952 --> 01:11:48,258
[Uncle Choi Woo Shik]
Alright!

1879
01:11:48,258 --> 01:11:50,214
- Oh dear.
- Happy New Year!

1880
01:11:50,214 --> 01:11:52,600
- No, don't do it!
- Don't do it!

1881
01:11:52,600 --> 01:11:55,028
- No, don't do it!
- Don't do it!

1882
01:11:55,028 --> 01:11:58,158
[We can't give New Year's money...]
- No, don't do it! - Don't do it!

1883
01:11:58,158 --> 01:12:00,645
- No, don't do it!
- Don't do it! Don't come!

1884
01:12:00,645 --> 01:12:03,553
[Instead of New Year's money, it's high fives]
High five, high five!

1885
01:12:03,553 --> 01:12:05,051
[Seo Jun fills our empty hands again]
High five!

1886
01:12:05,051 --> 01:12:07,751
- Okay.
- Okay, grow up healthy!

1887
01:12:07,751 --> 01:12:09,827
Sorry, we have no allowance to give...

1888
01:12:09,827 --> 01:12:12,369
[Sorry, Seo Jun]
We can't give anything...

1889
01:12:12,369 --> 01:12:14,847
[The cute little Seo Jun leaves as well...]
This is so funny.

1890
01:12:14,847 --> 01:12:16,220
Alright, then...

1891
01:12:16,220 --> 01:12:18,298
[Time for the trio to leave!]

1892
01:12:18,298 --> 01:12:19,660
Let's go find the car and leave!

1893
01:12:19,660 --> 01:12:21,007
Yeah.

1894
01:12:21,007 --> 01:12:22,131
[Heading to pick up the car]
- It's there. - Is it here?

1895
01:12:22,131 --> 01:12:24,400
- Yeah.
- It's right in front of Gwanghallu Garden.

1896
01:12:24,400 --> 01:12:26,437
- It's close.
- Yeah.

1897
01:12:26,437 --> 01:12:29,858
[17-min walk to car-sharing zone]
Oh, then this would be better.

1898
01:12:29,858 --> 01:12:31,972
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

1899
01:12:31,972 --> 01:12:34,814
[Thanks for the nice rest]

1900
01:12:34,814 --> 01:12:38,040
Let's do this!

1901
01:12:38,040 --> 01:12:41,233
We just need to go to
Namwon East Paid Parking Lot.

1902
01:12:41,233 --> 01:12:43,022
[With a phone, finding the way is easy]

1903
01:12:43,022 --> 01:12:46,876
[As they pick up the pace walking...]

1904
01:12:46,876 --> 01:12:48,491
Okay!

1905
01:12:48,491 --> 01:12:50,420
12 minutes on foot!

1906
01:12:50,420 --> 01:12:51,881
[Check]

1907
01:12:51,881 --> 01:12:53,194
Turn left!

1908
01:12:53,194 --> 01:12:55,338
- Turn left!
- Turn left.

1909
01:12:55,338 --> 01:12:56,439
[Check again]

1910
01:12:56,439 --> 01:12:58,608
I think we can go this way.

1911
01:12:58,608 --> 01:13:00,837
[But why that tone...]

1912
01:13:00,837 --> 01:13:03,053
Let's turn left now.

1913
01:13:03,053 --> 01:13:04,939
But Seo Jun, this is the right way, huh?

1914
01:13:04,939 --> 01:13:06,246
Yeah, turn left here!

1915
01:13:06,246 --> 01:13:08,362
[We've got digital, no worries]
We just need to go straight.

1916
01:13:08,362 --> 01:13:10,433
What? This is the dead-end.

1917
01:13:10,433 --> 01:13:11,484
What is it?

1918
01:13:11,484 --> 01:13:13,526
[Betrayed by the civilization they trusted...]

1919
01:13:13,526 --> 01:13:15,576
Oh, we went one block too far.

1920
01:13:15,576 --> 01:13:16,806
Hey...

1921
01:13:16,806 --> 01:13:18,719
- What are you doing?
- Oh, sorry.

1922
01:13:18,719 --> 01:13:20,716
- Oh, sorry.
- Hey...

1923
01:13:20,716 --> 01:13:22,058
[Final check]

1924
01:13:22,058 --> 01:13:24,054
This is the right place, huh?

1925
01:13:24,054 --> 01:13:26,644
[Director Choi inserts a shot]
Look, East Parking Lot.

1926
01:13:26,644 --> 01:13:29,238
[Congrats!
Safe arrival at the car-sharing zone]

1927
01:13:29,238 --> 01:13:30,526
I think that's it.

1928
01:13:30,526 --> 01:13:31,538
Isn't this it?

1929
01:13:31,538 --> 01:13:33,117
- Car-sharing reserved parking!
- This is it!

1930
01:13:33,117 --> 01:13:35,225
[Found the reserved car]
- Oh, this is it. - This one.

1931
01:13:35,225 --> 01:13:36,979
- But how do we get to this?
- This...

1932
01:13:36,979 --> 01:13:39,189
[I reserved it, but it's my first time...]
There's a notification.

1933
01:13:39,189 --> 01:13:41,922
[In the end, private tutoring from Po-po]
[Glancing]

1934
01:13:41,922 --> 01:13:44,074
Now you have to take pictures here!

1935
01:13:44,074 --> 01:13:45,849
- Take exterior shots.
- Yeah, front...

1936
01:13:45,849 --> 01:13:48,420
You have to follow what it tells you to shoot.

1937
01:13:48,420 --> 01:13:51,027
[Faithfully following the instructions]
And then...

1938
01:13:51,027 --> 01:13:53,028
And then the side!

1939
01:13:54,034 --> 01:13:55,719
[Struggling]

1940
01:13:55,719 --> 01:13:58,240
[The tutor handles the rest]

1941
01:13:58,240 --> 01:14:00,257
Back!

1942
01:14:00,257 --> 01:14:03,099
[Steady shutter work]

1943
01:14:03,099 --> 01:14:04,453
I've done this a few times.

1944
01:14:04,453 --> 01:14:06,726
[Adopter "Forty"]

1945
01:14:06,726 --> 01:14:09,644
Oh, it's opening now! It's open!

1946
01:14:09,644 --> 01:14:11,456
- Open the door.
- Done? Yeah.

1947
01:14:11,456 --> 01:14:13,265
- Oh, yeah!
- Take your bag off!

1948
01:14:13,265 --> 01:14:15,691
- Yes, I'll take off my bag first.
- Your bag...

1949
01:14:15,691 --> 01:14:17,411
Freedom at last!

1950
01:14:17,411 --> 01:14:18,585
Jeez...

1951
01:14:18,585 --> 01:14:19,987
Anything you need to grab from here?

1952
01:14:19,987 --> 01:14:21,331
No.

1953
01:14:21,331 --> 01:14:24,294
[All packed and the trunk sealed]
Alright.

1954
01:14:24,294 --> 01:14:26,321
You're setting the navigation, right?

1955
01:14:26,321 --> 01:14:29,066
- Yeah, I set it!
- Okay!

1956
01:14:29,066 --> 01:14:32,195
[First, they'll stop by a mart,
then head to the lodging]

1957
01:14:32,195 --> 01:14:34,398
- Wow, it's so convenient having a car...
- This is so nice.

1958
01:14:34,398 --> 01:14:37,549
[Now all that's left is
a smooth ride for the trio]

1959
01:14:37,549 --> 01:14:42,492
This really feels like such a lucky day.

1960
01:14:42,492 --> 01:14:44,439
Wow, this is totally...

1961
01:14:44,439 --> 01:14:47,590
[Through the changing scenery...]
- The place is way inside. - Yeah.

1962
01:14:47,590 --> 01:14:50,892
It kinda feels like a scene
from a movie right now.

1963
01:14:50,892 --> 01:14:51,958
Right.

1964
01:14:51,958 --> 01:14:54,430
There's a Namwon tunnel.

1965
01:14:54,430 --> 01:14:56,032
Seo Jun, we're going to the right place, huh?

1966
01:14:56,032 --> 01:14:59,175
I think we're going somewhere weird.

1967
01:14:59,175 --> 01:15:01,744
Why does it feel like
all the lights are off in the village?

1968
01:15:01,744 --> 01:15:06,706
[Unexpected twists always come
when you least expect them...]

1969
01:15:07,631 --> 01:15:08,732
Whoa...

1970
01:15:08,732 --> 01:15:10,032
[What will be the trio's fate?]

1971
01:15:10,032 --> 01:15:12,133
[Next week]

1972
01:15:12,133 --> 01:15:14,698
[Arriving at Seo Jun's acquaintance's house]
- This is the place. - Wow!

1973
01:15:14,698 --> 01:15:17,254
[Welcome, guys]
- This is amazing. Oh my gosh. - Wow!

1974
01:15:17,254 --> 01:15:19,236
[What got them excited]
- Whoa! - Whoa!

1975
01:15:19,236 --> 01:15:21,108
[A lodging full of old-house charm]
- This is so nice! - It's so nice inside here.

1976
01:15:21,108 --> 01:15:22,956
Wow, it's a full-on traditional hanok!

1977
01:15:22,956 --> 01:15:27,013
My feet are freezing... but it feels nice.

1978
01:15:27,013 --> 01:15:28,271
[Severe cold floor issue]

1979
01:15:28,271 --> 01:15:29,616
It's still warmer outside.

1980
01:15:29,616 --> 01:15:31,126
Oh, it's too cold!

1981
01:15:31,126 --> 01:15:32,459
Nice! I might get hemorrhoids.

1982
01:15:32,459 --> 01:15:34,306
[Retreating outside instead]
It's warmer outside.

1983
01:15:34,306 --> 01:15:36,022
[There aren't even any blankets]
Looks like there are no blankets.

1984
01:15:36,022 --> 01:15:38,137
- Really?
- What are we supposed to do with this?

1985
01:15:38,137 --> 01:15:39,433
[In the end]

1986
01:15:39,433 --> 01:15:41,233
[They raid the staff's lodging]
- Look, this place is nice! - Oh, it's nice!

1987
01:15:41,233 --> 01:15:42,308
Why is it so warm?

1988
01:15:42,308 --> 01:15:45,168
[A warm, modern lodging]
Whoa...

1989
01:15:45,168 --> 01:15:47,088
- We could throw a party here.
- It's super warm.

1990
01:15:47,088 --> 01:15:50,174
[Will they be able to spend a warm night?]
If it's too cold there, can we stay here?

1991
01:15:50,174 --> 01:15:51,382
[Thump!]

1992
01:15:51,382 --> 01:15:53,436
Now it finally feels like I'm traveling.

1993
01:15:53,436 --> 01:15:55,915
[Heading to the next destination refreshed]
- I'm excited for today. - Where should we go?

1994
01:15:55,915 --> 01:15:57,558
Oh, this place is beautiful!

1995
01:15:57,558 --> 01:15:59,661
[Embraced by green tea fields]
I'm really curious about the green tea.

1996
01:15:59,661 --> 01:16:01,060
[Alongside a calm seaside]
This kind of sea is new to me.

1997
01:16:01,060 --> 01:16:03,073
[They've arrived in Boseong]
This town is so cute.

1998
01:16:03,073 --> 01:16:05,553
- Can we have this? Really?
- Something this precious...

1999
01:16:05,553 --> 01:16:07,462
[Bread suddenly flies in]
Oh wow, thank you so much!

2000
01:16:07,462 --> 01:16:10,173
[Along with warm, friendly vibes]
Guess we're lucky with food today?

2001
01:16:10,173 --> 01:16:11,371
[The place they arrived at is]
I love Boseong.

2002
01:16:11,371 --> 01:16:14,029
[A vast tea plantation scented with green tea]
- Wow! - I've really wanted to come here.

2003
01:16:14,029 --> 01:16:16,386
[Excitedly, running around]

2004
01:16:16,386 --> 01:16:18,800
[Enjoying sweet and slightly bitter desserts]
Let's try some ice cream!

2005
01:16:18,800 --> 01:16:20,372
- With your girlfriend?
- Was it good?

2006
01:16:20,372 --> 01:16:21,577
I was really happy.

2007
01:16:21,577 --> 01:16:23,865
[My old flames come flooding back...]

2008
01:16:23,865 --> 01:16:25,141
Then have you ever carried her on your back?

2009
01:16:25,141 --> 01:16:27,201
I've carried her on my back plenty of times.
I did it all the time.

2010
01:16:27,201 --> 01:16:29,566
So when I put her down
after a piggyback ride, like this...

2011
01:16:30,359 --> 01:16:33,252
[Stories of past loves come along as a bonus]

2012
01:16:33,252 --> 01:16:34,512
It's been so long...

2013
01:16:34,512 --> 01:16:38,175
It's been so long
since she's actually touched the ground.
